WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:25.817 --> 00:00:27.944
♪ ♪

3
00:00:41.958 --> 00:00:44.044
(crowd clamoring)

4
00:00:46.212 --> 00:00:50.050
-(boot thumping)
-CROWD: One! Two! Three!

5
00:00:50.133 --> 00:00:51.843
(laughs menacingly)

6
00:00:51.926 --> 00:00:53.470
Yeah!

7
00:00:53.553 --> 00:00:55.430
(yells)

8
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:57.265
(yells. grunts)

9
00:00:57.432 --> 00:00:59.392
(cheering)

10
00:00:59.476 --> 00:01:01.061
Come on! Yeah!

11
00:01:03.605 --> 00:01:04.481
Come on!

12
00:01:04.564 --> 00:01:06.357
(yells)

13
00:01:06.483 --> 00:01:09.069
-(laughs)
-(crowd shouting)

14
00:01:13.406 --> 00:01:14.908
Let's do this! Come on!

15
00:01:15.116 --> 00:01:16.618
Come on!

16
00:01:16.743 --> 00:01:19.245
(yells. grunts)

17
00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:22.624
Come on! Come on!

18
00:01:22.832 --> 00:01:24.250
(chair clatters)

19
00:01:24.334 --> 00:01:26.002
(grunts) Come on.

20
00:01:26.169 --> 00:01:27.462
Let's do this. Come on.

21
00:01:27.629 --> 00:01:29.005
(crowd shouting)

22
00:01:29.172 --> 00:01:31.508
(wrestlers grunting)

23
00:01:36.179 --> 00:01:39.432
MAN: Let the backpack slip off
next time everyone stands.

24
00:01:45.772 --> 00:01:47.607
(cheering)

25
00:01:53.738 --> 00:01:54.823
Where's Jane?

26
00:01:54.948 --> 00:01:56.616
Daniel Kellner.

27
00:01:56.783 --> 00:01:59.077
Do you want to see her again
or not?

28
00:02:03.039 --> 00:02:05.792
(crowd cheering)

29
00:02:10.004 --> 00:02:11.464
Relax.

30
00:02:11.548 --> 00:02:12.924
Enjoy the match.

31
00:02:13.007 --> 00:02:15.176
Just got to make sure
it's all there.

32
00:02:15.385 --> 00:02:17.470
(crowd cheering)

33
00:02:19.556 --> 00:02:23.351
MAN 2:
7.23.48.83

34
00:02:23.393 --> 00:02:28.022
through 3.14.84A.

35
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:29.691
11.17.55...

36
00:02:29.816 --> 00:02:34.237
I make a total of 107
IronClad drives. 128 gig each.

37
00:02:34.362 --> 00:02:37.407
-You want me to do a recount?
-Uh. when we finish. yes.

38
00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:39.909
Printed documents
approximately 200 pages.

39
00:02:40.034 --> 00:02:41.452
What's the date range?

40
00:02:41.536 --> 00:02:43.496
Uh. we can catalog that
when we get back.

41
00:02:43.621 --> 00:02:46.166
But I'm seeing
as far back as 1947

42
00:02:46.249 --> 00:02:48.459
and as recent as last year.

43
00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:51.671
(door creaks open)

44
00:02:51.796 --> 00:02:53.840
(lively crowd chatter
in distance)

45
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:01.097
♪ ♪

46
00:03:14.611 --> 00:03:16.779
(breathing heavily)

47
00:03:28.416 --> 00:03:30.627
Well. this is all
rather disappointing.

48
00:03:33.254 --> 00:03:34.714
Where's Jane?

49
00:03:38.468 --> 00:03:40.553
(trembling breaths)

50
00:03:45.350 --> 00:03:47.143
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

51
00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:50.897
-DANIEL: Careful.
-(snips zip tie)

52
00:03:52.982 --> 00:03:54.901
-(Jane whimpering)
-Hey.

53
00:04:01.741 --> 00:04:03.451
Who turned you?

54
00:04:03.534 --> 00:04:07.705
Give me the names. all of them.
and you two can call a cab.

55
00:04:07.789 --> 00:04:09.749
It's here.

56
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:30.937
(backpack drops to ground)

57
00:04:32.855 --> 00:04:34.274
Where is it?

58
00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:40.863
-Put your weapon on the ground!
-(others shouting)

59
00:04:41.030 --> 00:04:44.284
Do not fire! Do not fire.

60
00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:47.245
If you fire.
it could activate the device.

61
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.124
Loosen your grip. Daniel.

62
00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.294
If you squeeze. it activates.
Soften your grip.

63
00:04:55.628 --> 00:04:57.505
Put it down.
You don't know how to use it.

64
00:04:57.672 --> 00:04:59.799
-I know how you used it.
-And it almost killed me.

65
00:04:59.924 --> 00:05:03.261
Now. place the device
on the ground.

66
00:05:03.344 --> 00:05:05.388
I should do to you
what you did to them.

67
00:05:05.555 --> 00:05:07.390
Stand down. Serena.

68
00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:10.143
(breathing heavily)

69
00:05:11.102 --> 00:05:14.230
Do not exert any pressure on it.

70
00:05:14.397 --> 00:05:16.774
Just loosen your grip.

71
00:05:16.899 --> 00:05:18.401
Loosen your grip. That's it.

72
00:05:18.526 --> 00:05:19.986
Just open your hand.

73
00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:22.155
That's it.

74
00:05:22.238 --> 00:05:23.990
Okay. Okay.

75
00:05:25.742 --> 00:05:27.994
Sweep everything into
the backpack and get in the car.

76
00:05:28.077 --> 00:05:29.620
Please. Jane.

77
00:05:32.123 --> 00:05:33.666
Get out.

78
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.174
You're not running
some malware op.

79
00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:43.926
You can't hide behind a screen
in your SCIF.

80
00:05:44.052 --> 00:05:45.470
The world is on the brink.

81
00:05:45.553 --> 00:05:47.722
Do you actually believe
that dumping inventory

82
00:05:47.764 --> 00:05:50.433
will be anything more
than a dangerous distraction?

83
00:05:51.642 --> 00:05:53.353
I watched the interrogations.

84
00:05:54.395 --> 00:05:55.813
History doesn't have
a reset key.

85
00:05:55.897 --> 00:05:57.690
If you do this.
there's no undoing it.

86
00:05:59.776 --> 00:06:01.694
That's the plan.

87
00:06:02.528 --> 00:06:03.654
(engine starts)

88
00:06:05.698 --> 00:06:07.992
(tires squealing)

89
00:06:15.249 --> 00:06:17.043
Boyd.

90
00:06:21.089 --> 00:06:23.049
He sits at a desk.

91
00:06:24.258 --> 00:06:26.177
How did he beat you?

92
00:06:34.977 --> 00:06:36.604
They said you committed treason?

93
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:38.147
It's not treason.
They're not the government.

94
00:06:38.272 --> 00:06:39.649
and they lie for a living.

95
00:06:39.857 --> 00:06:41.484
What is going on. Daniel?

96
00:06:41.692 --> 00:06:42.985
Their cars have trackers.

97
00:06:43.027 --> 00:06:44.320
We got to get rid of this.

98
00:06:44.529 --> 00:06:45.696
Please just take me home.

99
00:06:45.863 --> 00:06:47.907
They'd be waiting
at your apartment.

100
00:06:48.032 --> 00:06:50.201
Hey. hand me
the clear plastic bag.

101
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:55.665
Okay. Steer for a second.

102
00:06:57.166 --> 00:06:59.585
Okay. Okay.

103
00:07:02.422 --> 00:07:03.714
(dialing phone)

104
00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:05.925
-Okay. okay.
-(line ringing)

105
00:07:06.008 --> 00:07:07.468
Hugo. I'm clear.

106
00:07:07.635 --> 00:07:10.138
HUGO (over phone):
Daniel. I'm so proud of you.

107
00:07:10.221 --> 00:07:12.390
They kidnapped Jane
to get to me.

108
00:07:12.473 --> 00:07:14.142
She's with me now.

109
00:07:14.225 --> 00:07:15.810
HUGO:
Is she all right?

110
00:07:15.935 --> 00:07:17.520
Not really. Hugo.

111
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:18.855
Where do I do the drop?

112
00:07:18.938 --> 00:07:20.565
-No drop yet.
-(power tools buzzing)

113
00:07:20.648 --> 00:07:22.567
-Get secure. and then...
-DANIEL: No. no. no.

114
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.444
Send the guy for the bag now.

115
00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:26.320
Somebody needs to run
with this thing.

116
00:07:26.529 --> 00:07:27.780
That's you.

117
00:07:27.864 --> 00:07:29.365
You've got the ball.

118
00:07:30.408 --> 00:07:32.160
I don't want the ball.

119
00:07:32.285 --> 00:07:34.912
No. the plan was I get it out
of the facility. and I-I did.

120
00:07:34.996 --> 00:07:36.539
HUGO: I decided
you were best qualified

121
00:07:36.664 --> 00:07:37.999
to keep the material safe.

122
00:07:38.082 --> 00:07:40.084
Are you out of your mind?

123
00:07:40.209 --> 00:07:42.628
No. I'm not a field guy. Hugo.

124
00:07:42.670 --> 00:07:44.881
I-I did the tech work.
That's all I can do.

125
00:07:45.047 --> 00:07:46.007
You just stay with me.

126
00:07:46.215 --> 00:07:47.467
We're on plan.

127
00:07:47.675 --> 00:07:50.136
Waiting now for someone else
to be activated.

128
00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:52.472
When they are.
we'll know what comes next.

129
00:07:52.513 --> 00:07:55.141
Leave Jane somewhere safe
and get secure for the night.

130
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:57.894
Oh. no.
I-I'm not leaving her alone.

131
00:07:57.977 --> 00:08:00.563
-She'll be safer without you.
-But she wasn't.

132
00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:03.524
I'm gonna need you to drop
a marker when you get secure.

133
00:08:03.691 --> 00:08:05.860
Our friend Santiago
will find you in the morning.

134
00:08:06.027 --> 00:08:09.322
I should just dump everything
online right now.

135
00:08:11.032 --> 00:08:14.285
You cannot. under any
circumstances. do that.

136
00:08:15.828 --> 00:08:17.079
For now. we wait.

137
00:08:17.288 --> 00:08:19.081
Stay alert. Find shelter.

138
00:08:19.207 --> 00:08:21.334
Santiago will put us together
in the morning.

139
00:08:22.251 --> 00:08:23.544
Destroy your phone.

140
00:08:23.669 --> 00:08:24.962
(sighs)

141
00:08:25.087 --> 00:08:26.506
(siren wailing in distance)

142
00:08:26.631 --> 00:08:27.924
Danny.

143
00:08:28.132 --> 00:08:30.343
Satellite burner phones.

144
00:08:30.468 --> 00:08:31.928
They got their own
encrypted network.

145
00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:33.846
We only use them once.

146
00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:38.601
What exactly do you do
for a living?

147
00:08:39.810 --> 00:08:41.395
We got to get secure
for the night.

148
00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:43.314
No apartments. no motels.

149
00:08:43.397 --> 00:08:46.317
Has to be somewhere I've never
been before in my life.

150
00:08:47.610 --> 00:08:49.987
I know a place close to here.

151
00:09:01.666 --> 00:09:02.833
(elevator bell chimes)

152
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:05.878
Musgrave at DoD wants
a briefing.

153
00:09:06.003 --> 00:09:08.047
SCANLON:
Get Wakefield down here now.

154
00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:09.924
Tell Musgrave
it was a minor breach.

155
00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:11.384
Recovery is in process.

156
00:09:11.509 --> 00:09:13.344
Sir. he will not want
to hear it from me.

157
00:09:13.469 --> 00:09:15.429
If I pick up the phone.
it means I'm concerned.

158
00:09:15.555 --> 00:09:17.390
If they even get a whiff
of that. we'll have the entire

159
00:09:17.431 --> 00:09:19.767
military and intelligence
apparatus up here in an hour.

160
00:09:19.976 --> 00:09:21.227
Handle him.

161
00:09:21.352 --> 00:09:22.895
Anything relevant to this
on news feeds?

162
00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:24.272
Not yet.

163
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:25.940
Socials or secure private?

164
00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:27.733
All quiet.

165
00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:32.989
12 no-shows here today.

166
00:09:36.450 --> 00:09:38.327
All with empty desks.

167
00:09:38.369 --> 00:09:40.621
All clearance above G5.

168
00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:42.915
(busy chatter)

169
00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:51.924
All right. so we're dealing
with an operation

170
00:09:52.091 --> 00:09:55.344
carefully coordinated
and executed.

171
00:09:56.637 --> 00:09:59.223
Why? With what goal?

172
00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:00.891
If they wanted the archive out.

173
00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:02.351
Kellner would have
already released it.

174
00:10:02.476 --> 00:10:03.853
but he hasn't. which means

175
00:10:03.978 --> 00:10:05.688
somebody's maintaining
decision space.

176
00:10:05.813 --> 00:10:09.483
But for how long. we don't know.
so think quickly.

177
00:10:09.567 --> 00:10:11.110
Daniel Kellner has a doctorate

178
00:10:11.193 --> 00:10:12.862
in theoretical
and applied cybersecurity.

179
00:10:12.945 --> 00:10:14.739
and he's spent the better part
of eight years

180
00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:16.365
safeguarding high-side data.

181
00:10:16.407 --> 00:10:18.284
so what does that
tell us about him?

182
00:10:18.492 --> 00:10:19.535
Ideas.

183
00:10:19.660 --> 00:10:20.661
-Come on.
-He built the firewalls.

184
00:10:20.703 --> 00:10:22.163
He knows how to breach them.

185
00:10:22.371 --> 00:10:23.748
They're already breached.
We got to play past that.

186
00:10:23.831 --> 00:10:25.207
AGENT: We got to maintain
standard skip tracing.

187
00:10:25.249 --> 00:10:26.626
AGENT 2:
Well. I can access SYNTRAK.

188
00:10:26.751 --> 00:10:28.336
SERENA:
What's the next thing he does?

189
00:10:28.502 --> 00:10:30.671
BOYD:
Sir.

190
00:10:30.796 --> 00:10:33.758
Hugo Wakefield didn't show up
for work this morning.

191
00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:38.262
(sighs)
His desk was cleaned out.

192
00:10:38.346 --> 00:10:40.056
Hugo?

193
00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:46.228
Second device is missing
from deep storage.

194
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:48.105
Where's the third?

195
00:10:48.230 --> 00:10:50.066
Locked down in the cold room.

196
00:10:54.028 --> 00:10:56.155
♪ ♪

197
00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:18.177
♪ ♪

198
00:11:25.309 --> 00:11:26.644
(vehicle door closes)

199
00:11:30.648 --> 00:11:33.442
DANIEL: How do you know
they'll answer it?

200
00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:35.444
'Cause that's what we do.

201
00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:38.155
How do you know this place?

202
00:11:42.660 --> 00:11:44.203
Jane.

203
00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:48.290
(sobbing):
Oh... oh. my dear.

204
00:11:52.420 --> 00:11:54.797
The monsignor has finally
surrendered his sneakers.

205
00:11:54.964 --> 00:11:56.298
-Oh.
-(chuckling)

206
00:11:56.340 --> 00:11:57.883
Oh. I couldn't bear
his other shoes.

207
00:11:58.008 --> 00:12:00.261
I know. They always
squeaked so horribly.

208
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:01.429
(both laughing)

209
00:12:01.554 --> 00:12:04.056
(imitating squeaking footsteps)

210
00:12:04.181 --> 00:12:07.601
Oh. we have missed you
very much. my dear.

211
00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:09.478
Oh. come on.

212
00:12:09.603 --> 00:12:11.397
All I ever did was drive you
and the other sisters crazy.

213
00:12:11.439 --> 00:12:15.109
Mm. well. you do ask
a lot of questions.

214
00:12:15.234 --> 00:12:17.153
Did Teresa ever get through
her postulancy?

215
00:12:17.278 --> 00:12:18.571
She sailed through.

216
00:12:18.696 --> 00:12:20.740
Once she stopped
sneaking out at night.

217
00:12:20.823 --> 00:12:22.283
JANE:
No.

218
00:12:22.408 --> 00:12:23.367
SISTER MAURA:
The monsignor has her teaching

219
00:12:23.534 --> 00:12:25.369
third grade at St. Anthony's.

220
00:12:25.453 --> 00:12:27.621
JANE: Oh. she'll be
fantastic with kids.

221
00:12:27.705 --> 00:12:30.082
BOTH:
Saint Benedicta.

222
00:12:32.668 --> 00:12:35.671
Hold this against your eye.

223
00:12:43.095 --> 00:12:45.347
I'm not going to ask you
any questions.

224
00:12:45.514 --> 00:12:46.891
It's not my business.

225
00:12:47.016 --> 00:12:48.976
But Jane is.

226
00:12:50.019 --> 00:12:53.689
Whatever you have done. you must
hold yourself accountable.

227
00:12:53.898 --> 00:12:57.026
But leave Jane out of it.

228
00:12:57.067 --> 00:12:59.445
She can stay with us.

229
00:13:04.241 --> 00:13:05.951
(chuckling):
You were a nun?

230
00:13:07.286 --> 00:13:09.705
We've had sex.
What do you think?

231
00:13:09.872 --> 00:13:13.459
I think everything you told me
about yourself isn't true.

232
00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:16.754
You have an enormous
amount of nerve.

233
00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:19.006
Yeah. I kept things to myself

234
00:13:19.131 --> 00:13:21.675
because I had to sign away
my life. but your thing...

235
00:13:21.759 --> 00:13:24.512
(chuckles)
You were an actual nun?

236
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.472
A novitiate.

237
00:13:26.555 --> 00:13:27.681
Why didn't you say anything?

238
00:13:27.765 --> 00:13:29.183
I omitted a portion of my story.

239
00:13:29.308 --> 00:13:30.476
People judge you.

240
00:13:33.354 --> 00:13:35.397
When was all this?

241
00:13:36.357 --> 00:13:37.858
Three years ago.

242
00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:41.111
And I'm not answering
any more questions until you do.

243
00:13:42.738 --> 00:13:44.323
What did you steal?

244
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.411
I stole the data
they paid me to protect.

245
00:13:49.537 --> 00:13:51.330
Why would you do that?

246
00:13:52.498 --> 00:13:54.416
'Cause people have a right
to know the truth.

247
00:13:55.501 --> 00:13:58.796
And what is it.
this truth you stole?

248
00:14:00.881 --> 00:14:02.758
So...

249
00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:06.846
you wanted to be a nun.
but what. you lost your faith?

250
00:14:07.721 --> 00:14:09.515
I lost my calling.

251
00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:12.393
How long have you worked
for these people?

252
00:14:12.560 --> 00:14:14.311
Since. um...

253
00:14:18.065 --> 00:14:20.442
Since I got out...

254
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:22.820
of federal prison
eight years ago.

255
00:14:26.699 --> 00:14:31.078
I did 19 months in Petersburg
for cybercrimes.

256
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:33.581
WARDEX recruited me
straight out of the parking lot

257
00:14:33.706 --> 00:14:35.583
the day I was released.

258
00:14:35.749 --> 00:14:38.168
-Even with your record?
-Because of my record.

259
00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:40.462
I keep secrets for a living.

260
00:14:40.588 --> 00:14:43.883
I-I didn't mean
to keep them from you.

261
00:14:43.924 --> 00:14:47.636
Three months ago. I didn't know
half of what I know now.

262
00:14:49.221 --> 00:14:50.723
Jane...

263
00:14:52.516 --> 00:14:54.476
I'm doing the right thing.

264
