00:35:11.776 --> 00:35:12.902
-Got to go. Got to go.
-What?

756
00:35:13.069 --> 00:35:14.278
-Got to go.
-What are you talk...

757
00:35:14.403 --> 00:35:15.530
-Oh. God. I'm so sorry.
-Hi. Uh...

758
00:35:15.613 --> 00:35:16.739
-Excuse me.
-What do you mean?

759
00:35:16.948 --> 00:35:18.491
-You mean busting out?
-Yep.

760
00:35:18.574 --> 00:35:19.867
-Wh-What's wrong with you?
-What's wrong is I have

761
00:35:19.992 --> 00:35:21.869
a very uncooperative
boyfriend right...

762
00:35:25.206 --> 00:35:27.792
-Oh. you got to be kidding me.
-What? What did I do?

763
00:35:28.000 --> 00:35:29.460
You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

764
00:35:29.585 --> 00:35:31.420
What did I do? Maggie.

765
00:35:32.672 --> 00:35:33.840
Shoes. Shoes. shoes.

766
00:35:33.965 --> 00:35:35.383
Yeah. sure.

767
00:35:35.591 --> 00:35:37.301
-Here.
-Thank you.

768
00:35:39.387 --> 00:35:41.472
How's it going?

769
00:35:49.522 --> 00:35:51.649
♪ ♪

770
00:35:59.490 --> 00:36:01.159
WARDEX?

771
00:36:01.242 --> 00:36:04.829
Stands for Waived Reporting
Development and Extraction.

772
00:36:06.038 --> 00:36:07.665
Of what?

773
00:36:24.807 --> 00:36:28.769
Homestead Air Force Base
in Florida. 1973.

774
00:36:29.812 --> 00:36:31.439
Who's the guy with Nixon?

775
00:36:31.564 --> 00:36:33.191
Big TV star in the '50s.

776
00:36:33.274 --> 00:36:35.276
Nixon wanted to impress him.

777
00:36:44.410 --> 00:36:46.537
♪ ♪

778
00:37:05.932 --> 00:37:08.059
♪ ♪

779
00:37:22.949 --> 00:37:24.742
Are they children?

780
00:37:24.909 --> 00:37:26.410
No.

781
00:37:29.497 --> 00:37:32.416
Are they... people?

782
00:37:32.583 --> 00:37:34.418
No.

783
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:39.674
Are they human?

784
00:37:52.728 --> 00:37:54.897
This next part's hard to watch.

785
00:37:56.440 --> 00:37:59.277
It's what Hugo showed me
that got me into this.

786
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:02.071
Okay?

787
00:38:07.827 --> 00:38:09.412
Okay.

788
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:12.206
(taps key)

789
00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:13.958
MED TECH 1 (on video):
We're gonna need vitals.

790
00:38:14.041 --> 00:38:15.584
-We've got no baseline.
-(overlapping chatter on video)

791
00:38:15.626 --> 00:38:17.003
MED TECH 2:
Pulse ox can't read.

792
00:38:17.169 --> 00:38:18.671
-No standard landmarks...
-MED TECH 3: Ketamine?

793
00:38:18.879 --> 00:38:20.089
-Four to six milligrams?
-SCANLON: No more sedatives.

794
00:38:20.256 --> 00:38:21.841
I want baseline
stress data first.

795
00:38:22.008 --> 00:38:23.884
MED TECH 4: Shift your grip.
Secure the ankles.

796
00:38:24.010 --> 00:38:26.429
-(clicking vocalizations)
-Stabilize head and right arm.

797
00:38:26.470 --> 00:38:28.764
(shrieks)

798
00:38:28.931 --> 00:38:30.725
(distressed shrieking. clicking)

799
00:38:30.808 --> 00:38:32.226
MED TECH 3:
Head's moving too much.

800
00:38:32.268 --> 00:38:33.811
I need a padded restraint.

801
00:38:33.894 --> 00:38:35.938
SCANLON: I have it.
I need cerebrospinal fluid.

802
00:38:36.105 --> 00:38:38.441
Advance the needle
18 centimeters.

803
00:38:38.482 --> 00:38:40.234
-ventral to the medulla.
-(shuddering breaths)

804
00:38:40.359 --> 00:38:42.445
MED TECH 1: It's in distress.
Administering propofol.

805
00:38:42.611 --> 00:38:44.530
SCANLON:
Negative. No anesthesia.

806
00:38:44.613 --> 00:38:46.657
We lost one that way. Do it now.

807
00:38:46.741 --> 00:38:47.950
Insert it now.

808
00:38:48.034 --> 00:38:49.869
(pained shrieking)

809
00:38:50.077 --> 00:38:51.662
(shrieking stops)

810
00:38:51.746 --> 00:38:54.915
(shuddering breaths)

811
00:39:04.091 --> 00:39:05.509
There's more.

812
00:39:05.634 --> 00:39:08.679
79 years more.

813
00:39:10.681 --> 00:39:12.391
I have all of it.

814
00:39:12.558 --> 00:39:15.144
(whirring)

815
00:39:17.396 --> 00:39:19.482
(electronic trilling)

816
00:39:21.025 --> 00:39:23.361
(buzzing)

817
00:39:34.789 --> 00:39:38.000
Hugo is the only one
who had a relationship with it.

818
00:39:38.042 --> 00:39:40.586
and he knew what he was doing
with that thing.

819
00:39:40.669 --> 00:39:42.713
Pull up Kellner's data.

820
00:39:47.968 --> 00:39:49.303
Give me the device.

821
00:39:49.428 --> 00:39:50.888
BOYD:
If systolic goes below 90

822
00:39:51.055 --> 00:39:52.390
like last time.
I'm pulling you out.

823
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:53.891
MED TECH:
Watch for tachyarrhythmia.

824
00:39:53.933 --> 00:39:55.601
-subdural hemorrhage.
-MED TECH 2: Copy.

825
00:39:55.810 --> 00:39:58.187
(monitor beeping)

826
00:39:59.480 --> 00:40:01.399
(quiet chatter)

827
00:40:01.524 --> 00:40:03.651
♪ ♪

828
00:40:11.450 --> 00:40:14.078
(beeping growing faster)

829
00:40:16.122 --> 00:40:17.289
(whimpers)

830
00:40:17.331 --> 00:40:20.000
(yells. groans)

831
00:40:20.167 --> 00:40:22.294
I'm fine. I'm fine!

832
00:40:22.336 --> 00:40:24.046
What happened?

833
00:40:26.215 --> 00:40:28.551
I had focus. gave myself over.

834
00:40:28.634 --> 00:40:31.345
saw Kellner for a split second.
then...

835
00:40:31.554 --> 00:40:33.013
sledgehammer. whiteout.

836
00:40:33.097 --> 00:40:35.516
Sucked all the air
out of my lungs.

837
00:40:35.724 --> 00:40:37.643
Is he an experiencer?

838
00:40:37.768 --> 00:40:39.437
You can't dive on them.

839
00:40:41.730 --> 00:40:43.983
He can't have been.
I'd have known.

840
00:40:44.191 --> 00:40:45.776
He's Hugo's guy.

841
00:40:45.901 --> 00:40:48.154
There's gonna be a whole lot
we don't know.

842
00:40:48.362 --> 00:40:51.031
Maybe. but I'm not going
back in there to find out.

843
00:41:01.083 --> 00:41:03.294
Pull the data on the girlfriend.

844
00:41:04.670 --> 00:41:08.466
There have been retrieval
programs of exotic craft.

845
00:41:09.467 --> 00:41:12.970
Interrogation
of nonhuman biologics.

846
00:41:13.053 --> 00:41:16.182
Reverse engineering
and technology exploitation.

847
00:41:16.348 --> 00:41:17.808
All of it...

848
00:41:17.975 --> 00:41:20.728
run by WARDEX.
the Department of Defense

849
00:41:20.936 --> 00:41:23.022
and the defense industry.

850
00:41:23.105 --> 00:41:25.608
It has the highest level
of military

851
00:41:25.649 --> 00:41:27.151
and private sector
classification

852
00:41:27.234 --> 00:41:28.569
in American history.

853
00:41:28.777 --> 00:41:29.945
(wind howling outside)

854
00:41:30.112 --> 00:41:31.447
They've run it
since the early '70s

855
00:41:31.572 --> 00:41:32.823
without government funding.

856
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:34.867
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

857
00:41:35.034 --> 00:41:37.369
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

858
00:41:37.536 --> 00:41:39.121
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

859
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:42.041
especially after
the Nixon thing.

860
00:41:42.166 --> 00:41:45.753
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

861
00:41:45.878 --> 00:41:49.173
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

862
00:41:51.175 --> 00:41:54.512
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

863
00:41:55.596 --> 00:41:59.058
This all stops now.

864
00:41:59.141 --> 00:42:00.726
What are you gonna do?

865
00:42:01.769 --> 00:42:06.440
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

866
00:42:09.193 --> 00:42:12.154
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

867
00:42:13.280 --> 00:42:15.032
On everything?

868
00:42:16.033 --> 00:42:17.368
What...

869
00:42:17.493 --> 00:42:19.203
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

870
00:42:19.245 --> 00:42:22.081
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

871
00:42:22.289 --> 00:42:25.000
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

872
00:42:25.084 --> 00:42:27.378
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

873
00:42:27.503 --> 00:42:29.255
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

874
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:31.757
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

875
00:42:31.882 --> 00:42:34.510
this core truth
about the universe.

876
00:42:34.635 --> 00:42:36.887
-It's wrong.
-You can't do that.

877
00:42:38.013 --> 00:42:39.723
Think about...

878
00:42:41.308 --> 00:42:42.685
People will see them as deities.

879
00:42:42.768 --> 00:42:44.812
-They'll stop believing in God.
-(scoffs)

880
00:42:44.853 --> 00:42:46.689
Well. you left the church.

881
00:42:46.814 --> 00:42:48.148
Not because I stopped believing.

882
00:42:48.232 --> 00:42:49.817
because I could no longer say
with certainty

883
00:42:49.984 --> 00:42:51.235
that God is divine.

884
00:42:51.360 --> 00:42:54.572
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

885
00:42:56.323 --> 00:42:57.783
He's how we define ourselves.

886
00:42:57.950 --> 00:43:00.911
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

887
00:43:02.288 --> 00:43:05.082
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

888
00:43:05.207 --> 00:43:08.961
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

889
00:43:09.044 --> 00:43:10.879
People can't handle both.

890
00:43:13.340 --> 00:43:14.967
Of course they can.

891
00:43:15.175 --> 00:43:16.594
No. they can't.

892
00:43:17.595 --> 00:43:19.680
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

893
00:43:20.681 --> 00:43:25.019
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

894
00:43:26.478 --> 00:43:31.066
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

895
00:43:35.237 --> 00:43:37.448
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

896
00:43:49.168 --> 00:43:50.919
No signal.

897
00:43:52.671 --> 00:43:54.298
No signal.

898
00:43:54.465 --> 00:43:56.717
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

899
00:44:09.938 --> 00:44:12.316
(door opens and closes)

900
00:44:14.234 --> 00:44:16.403
(Jackson grunting. panting)

901
00:44:21.367 --> 00:44:23.577
(thunder rumbling)

902
00:44:26.622 --> 00:44:27.790
-Okay.
-(knocking)

903
00:44:27.998 --> 00:44:29.249
-Unlock the door!
-(engine starts)

904
00:44:29.416 --> 00:44:30.626
-What?
-Jackson. come on!

905
00:44:30.668 --> 00:44:32.461
-(lock clicks)
-Oh. shit. Sorry.

906
00:44:33.587 --> 00:44:35.255
Oh. sorry. sorry.

907
00:44:35.422 --> 00:44:37.841
-Okay.
-Oh. my God.

908
00:44:39.593 --> 00:44:41.970
(phone ringing)

909
00:44:42.054 --> 00:44:43.555
(Jackson stammers)

910
00:44:43.681 --> 00:44:45.140
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

911
00:44:45.265 --> 00:44:46.517
I'm marching you
right back inside.

912
00:44:46.725 --> 00:44:48.227
Hello?

913
00:44:48.310 --> 00:44:50.187
HUGO (over phone): I've been
waiting a very long time

914
00:44:50.270 --> 00:44:52.481
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

915
00:44:52.606 --> 00:44:54.024
Who is this?

916
00:44:54.191 --> 00:44:55.859
A friend.

917
00:44:56.985 --> 00:44:59.738
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

918
00:44:59.822 --> 00:45:01.323
you'd know if I wasn't.

919
00:45:01.448 --> 00:45:02.783
No. I don't... I don't know you

920
00:45:02.866 --> 00:45:04.618
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

921
00:45:04.785 --> 00:45:06.912
HUGO: Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

922
00:45:07.079 --> 00:45:08.831
-I'm not managing it. I'm not.
-Who-who is that?

923
00:45:08.872 --> 00:45:11.291
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

924
00:45:11.417 --> 00:45:15.379
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

925
00:45:15.504 --> 00:45:17.256
-Let us help you get there.
-Help me how?

926
00:45:17.297 --> 00:45:18.298
What do you mean?

927
00:45:18.424 --> 00:45:19.717
-Is that the FBI?
-Shh!

928
00:45:19.925 --> 00:45:20.968
HUGO: We want to offer you
our protection.

929
00:45:21.135 --> 00:45:22.511
We held back on reaching out

930
00:45:22.594 --> 00:45:24.596
until after we saw
your weather report.

931
00:45:24.763 --> 00:45:25.889
You held back?

932
00:45:26.056 --> 00:45:27.141
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

933
00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:29.184
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

934
00:45:32.813 --> 00:45:35.816
Who is 873-2626?

935
00:45:37.317 --> 00:45:38.694
Since you know that number.

936
00:45:38.777 --> 00:45:41.238
you must already know
who it belongs to.

937
00:45:43.532 --> 00:45:44.867
Kellner?

938
00:45:45.784 --> 00:45:46.702
Kellner?

939
00:45:46.785 --> 00:45:48.620
All right.

940
00:45:48.662 --> 00:45:50.164
Listen carefully.

941
00:45:50.330 --> 00:45:51.582
You cannot go home.

942
00:45:51.707 --> 00:45:52.916
If you have another direction
in mind.

943
00:45:53.041 --> 00:45:55.252
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

944
00:45:55.461 --> 00:45:57.087
If we can find you by phone.
others can

945
00:45:57.254 --> 00:45:58.881
-find you in the world.
-No. it's too late.

946
00:45:59.047 --> 00:46:00.382
They...
Uh. they already found me.

947
00:46:00.466 --> 00:46:03.177
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

948
00:46:03.385 --> 00:46:04.720
How will you find me?

949
00:46:04.845 --> 00:46:06.054
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

950
00:46:06.138 --> 00:46:07.264
Do it now.

951
00:46:09.016 --> 00:46:11.894
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

952
00:46:13.395 --> 00:46:14.313
Back up over the phone.

953
00:46:14.480 --> 00:46:16.106
-What?
-Back up!

954
00:46:16.190 --> 00:46:17.775
-Come on. -Okay. I'd like
to point out that I'm being

955
00:46:17.858 --> 00:46:20.194
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

956
00:46:20.402 --> 00:46:22.446
and that was a $600 phone.

957
00:46:23.363 --> 00:46:25.324
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

958
00:46:25.491 --> 00:46:26.867
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

959
00:46:26.992 --> 00:46:28.076
-Come on.
-Sorry.

960
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:34.666
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

961
00:46:34.750 --> 00:46:36.877
-Okay. (mutters)
-What?

962
00:46:40.506 --> 00:46:41.965
Okay.

963
00:46:43.592 --> 00:46:46.053
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

964
00:46:47.596 --> 00:46:49.431
Keep going. Keep going.

965
00:46:58.649 --> 00:47:00.943
Okay. Okay.

966
00:47:01.026 --> 00:47:04.196
-Okay. let's go. Let's go.
-Uh... wh-where?

967
00:47:04.363 --> 00:47:05.948
-North.
-Why?

968
00:47:06.031 --> 00:47:07.324
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

969
00:47:07.449 --> 00:47:08.867
Oh. my God. (stammering)

970
00:47:08.992 --> 00:47:10.577
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

971
00:47:10.702 --> 00:47:12.120
-that you never told me about?
-I don't know. Jackson.

972
00:47:12.204 --> 00:47:13.455
-Or what is it?
-You're giving me a headache.

973
00:47:13.580 --> 00:47:14.414
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

974
00:47:14.581 --> 00:47:15.707
I don't know who he is.

975
00:47:15.791 --> 00:47:17.209
I just know
he's someplace north.

976
00:47:17.376 --> 00:47:18.460
-That's all I know. okay?
-(hailstones clacking)

977
00:47:18.585 --> 00:47:20.003
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

978
00:47:22.339 --> 00:47:24.383
-Your hailstorm.
-Wow.

979
00:47:24.591 --> 00:47:25.884
Weather Shimmy?

980
00:47:26.009 --> 00:47:28.345
Just drive. Just drive.

981
00:47:37.980 --> 00:47:40.190
(electronic trilling. beeping)

982
00:47:40.315 --> 00:47:42.484
♪ ♪

983
00:48:08.051 --> 00:48:09.887
(sighs)

984
00:48:10.846 --> 00:48:12.139
(electronic warbling)

985
00:48:12.347 --> 00:48:14.349
(crate thuds on table)

986
00:48:16.810 --> 00:48:19.396
You got Kellner on 2626.

987
00:48:21.064 --> 00:48:22.524
Look at the video
I just sent you.

988
00:48:22.691 --> 00:48:24.192
DANIEL (over phone):
Okay. hold on.

989
00:48:26.236 --> 00:48:28.363
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

990
00:48:30.574 --> 00:48:31.992
Yeah. So?

991
00:48:32.117 --> 00:48:33.994
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

992
00:48:34.119 --> 00:48:36.413
DANIEL:
Her? Why?

993
00:48:36.538 --> 00:48:38.749
Did you not hear her?

994
00:48:38.874 --> 00:48:40.334
DANIEL:
Yeah. I heard her.

995
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:41.752
And you still ask why?

996
00:48:41.919 --> 00:48:43.670
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

997
00:48:43.712 --> 00:48:45.589
That's all she had to say?

998
00:48:46.924 --> 00:48:49.009
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

999
00:48:49.134 --> 00:48:50.344
That's what she said?

1000
00:48:50.510 --> 00:48:52.095
You didn't hear it?

1001
00:48:53.555 --> 00:48:55.057
We all heard it.

1002
00:48:55.140 --> 00:48:57.225
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

1003
00:48:57.392 --> 00:48:58.894
(chuckling):
Of course it is.

1004
00:48:59.061 --> 00:49:00.979
I'm listening to it right now.

1005
00:49:01.146 --> 00:49:02.898
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

1006
00:49:03.023 --> 00:49:04.816
-We'll get a car to you.
Leave tonight. -Hey. wait.

1007
00:49:05.025 --> 00:49:06.568
-Wait a second. Wait a second.
-Do not travel by day.

1008
00:49:06.693 --> 00:49:07.945
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

1009
00:49:08.070 --> 00:49:09.071
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

1010
00:49:09.237 --> 00:49:10.364
DANIEL:
Hey. listen to me.

1011
00:49:10.405 --> 00:49:11.657
Have you played this
to other people?

1012
00:49:11.823 --> 00:49:13.784
Stay with me.

1013
00:49:13.867 --> 00:49:16.453
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

1014
00:49:16.578 --> 00:49:18.413
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

1015
00:49:18.538 --> 00:49:20.958
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

1016
00:49:21.124 --> 00:49:23.752
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

1017
00:49:23.877 --> 00:49:27.422
There are two of you. Daniel.

1018
00:49:27.506 --> 00:49:30.676
There's always been
just the two of you.

1019
00:49:30.842 --> 00:49:32.761
(rustling)

1020
00:49:32.844 --> 00:49:34.972
♪ ♪

1021
00:49:59.079 --> 00:50:00.831
(breathing heavily)

1022
00:50:02.249 --> 00:50:04.459
(pills rattling)

1023
00:50:10.007 --> 00:50:12.676
(gasping)

1024
00:50:12.759 --> 00:50:15.178
(trembling breaths)

1025
00:50:20.058 --> 00:50:21.476
(exhales slowly)

1026
00:50:24.104 --> 00:50:26.273
(trembling breaths continue)

1027
00:50:27.733 --> 00:50:29.526
(whirring)

1028
00:50:40.162 --> 00:50:42.706
♪ ♪

1029
00:50:43.790 --> 00:50:46.168
(muffled shattering)

1030
00:50:55.510 --> 00:50:58.221
(glass shards clinking)

1031
00:51:17.699 --> 00:51:19.826
♪ ♪

1032
00:51:29.544 --> 00:51:31.463
-(hands clap)
-(gasps)

1033
00:51:31.546 --> 00:51:33.715
(sharp. heavy breathing)

1034
00:51:39.638 --> 00:51:41.890
(praying in Latin)

1035
00:51:59.574 --> 00:52:01.701
♪ ♪

1036
00:52:26.059 --> 00:52:27.602
Hello. Jane.

1037
00:52:27.644 --> 00:52:29.604
Please.

1038
00:52:30.897 --> 00:52:32.983
Have a seat.

1039
00:52:38.572 --> 00:52:41.074
Where are you right now. Jane?

1040
00:52:41.283 --> 00:52:42.993
What is your location?

1041
00:52:44.161 --> 00:52:46.621
-I don't know.
-Relax. please.

1042
00:52:49.958 --> 00:52:52.502
-Who are you?
-I'll ask the questions.

1043
00:52:53.503 --> 00:52:55.338
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

1044
00:53:01.428 --> 00:53:02.846
He's outside.

1045
00:53:06.474 --> 00:53:08.143
Where were you last night?

1046
00:53:09.895 --> 00:53:11.980
(breath trembling)

1047
00:53:14.065 --> 00:53:15.358
(snarls)

1048
00:53:15.525 --> 00:53:17.527
(panting)

1049
00:53:17.611 --> 00:53:20.280
-BP's high but holding: 156/94.
-O2's decent at 96.

1050
00:53:20.405 --> 00:53:22.199
-but sodium's climbing.
-Heart rate's hot. too-- 118.

1051
00:53:22.365 --> 00:53:23.491
-Potassium's borderline. too.
-Jane!

1052
00:53:23.617 --> 00:53:25.202
-Stand by. Ringer's.
-Jane!

1053
00:53:26.119 --> 00:53:27.621
-Jane!
-(gasps)

1054
00:53:27.662 --> 00:53:30.040
Where were you last night?

1055
00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:34.169
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

1056
00:53:34.294 --> 00:53:36.421
Monastery St. Clare?

1057
00:53:36.546 --> 00:53:37.881
Of course.

1058
00:53:38.006 --> 00:53:41.009
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

1059
00:53:41.092 --> 00:53:43.011
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

1060
00:53:43.178 --> 00:53:45.722
and she had a vision
of it instead.

1061
00:53:45.889 --> 00:53:48.516
She was in two places at once.
like me.

1062
00:53:51.186 --> 00:53:53.188
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

1063
00:53:53.313 --> 00:53:55.232
13 miles southeast
of the District.

1064
00:53:55.398 --> 00:53:57.901
When you left.
which way did you drive?

1065
00:53:59.027 --> 00:54:01.404
(Jane's breath trembling)

1066
00:54:01.529 --> 00:54:02.781
I don't know.

1067
00:54:02.906 --> 00:54:04.532
Was the sun up?

1068
00:54:07.577 --> 00:54:08.912
Yes.

1069
00:54:09.079 --> 00:54:11.331
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

1070
00:54:14.668 --> 00:54:16.419
It was on the right.

1071
00:54:18.505 --> 00:54:19.923
I don't like you.

1072
00:54:20.048 --> 00:54:21.800
Not required.

1073
00:54:21.925 --> 00:54:23.260
Sun on the right.

1074
00:54:23.385 --> 00:54:25.178
Sun on the right--
they're headed due north.

1075
00:54:25.303 --> 00:54:26.429
possibly northwest.

1076
00:54:26.596 --> 00:54:28.348
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

1077
00:54:28.473 --> 00:54:29.766
Interstate not likely.

1078
00:54:29.933 --> 00:54:31.559
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

1079
00:54:31.685 --> 00:54:34.145
Did you pass a street sign?

1080
00:54:34.312 --> 00:54:35.772
JANE:
Yes.

1081
00:54:35.855 --> 00:54:37.607
What did it say?

1082
00:54:37.691 --> 00:54:39.859
(breath continues trembling)

1083
00:54:41.861 --> 00:54:45.115
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

1084
00:54:45.156 --> 00:54:47.659
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

1085
00:54:47.784 --> 00:54:50.287
AGENT: I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

1086
00:54:50.453 --> 00:54:53.665
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

1087
00:54:53.707 --> 00:54:55.667
Try for more details. Jane.

1088
00:54:55.750 --> 00:54:57.294
What else did you pass?

1089
00:54:57.377 --> 00:54:59.087
(breath continues trembling)

1090
00:54:59.170 --> 00:55:00.297
A river.

1091
00:55:00.380 --> 00:55:01.965
Passed a river.

1092
00:55:02.090 --> 00:55:04.259
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

1093
00:55:06.344 --> 00:55:08.596
-Yes.
-What did it say?

1094
00:55:10.056 --> 00:55:12.851
(whimpering)

1095
00:55:13.059 --> 00:55:14.561
S-Sykesville.

1096
00:55:14.728 --> 00:55:17.480
-Sykesville.
-Sykesville.

1097
00:55:18.648 --> 00:55:21.109
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

1098
00:55:21.234 --> 00:55:23.862
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

1099
00:55:23.945 --> 00:55:26.197
Maintain maximum legal speed.

1100
00:55:26.406 --> 00:55:29.242
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

1101
00:55:29.367 --> 00:55:30.952
-A few minutes.
-Few minutes.

1102
00:55:31.077 --> 00:55:32.912
Did you turn right or left?

1103
00:55:33.079 --> 00:55:34.581
-Right.
-Right.

1104
00:55:34.706 --> 00:55:37.334
Do you remember
the name of the road?

1105
00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:38.668
No.

1106
00:55:38.877 --> 00:55:40.837
Do you remember anything
about the road?

1107
00:55:41.921 --> 00:55:43.131
(breath continues trembling)

1108
00:55:43.214 --> 00:55:45.633
(whirring)

1109
00:55:47.469 --> 00:55:49.304
(breath stops trembling)

1110
00:55:49.429 --> 00:55:51.139
It was a dirt road.

1111
00:55:51.222 --> 00:55:52.682
Dirt road.

1112
00:55:52.849 --> 00:55:54.476
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

1113
00:55:54.642 --> 00:55:56.770
outside Sykesville. dead end.

1114
00:55:56.978 --> 00:55:58.396
Farmhouse at the end.

1115
00:55:58.563 --> 00:55:59.856
And found it.

1116
00:55:59.939 --> 00:56:01.274
Ash Hollow Road.

1117
00:56:01.441 --> 00:56:03.693
Target is a farmhouse.

1118
00:56:04.611 --> 00:56:06.946
(tires squealing)

1119
00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:12.786
You've done very well. Jane.

1120
00:56:12.827 --> 00:56:15.372
A service to your country.

1121
00:56:15.580 --> 00:56:18.708
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

1122
00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:23.004
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

1123
00:56:23.046 --> 00:56:25.548
you may need
to stop him yourself

1124
00:56:25.632 --> 00:56:27.634
any way you can.

1125
00:56:29.803 --> 00:56:32.472
(cries out in pain)

1126
00:56:34.057 --> 00:56:36.017
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

1127
00:56:36.101 --> 00:56:38.061
Uh. heart rate's dropping--
down to 59.

1128
00:56:38.144 --> 00:56:41.064
-Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.
-(Scanlon coughing)

1129
00:56:41.106 --> 00:56:44.067
(breathing deeply)

1130
00:56:45.693 --> 00:56:47.612
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

1131
00:56:47.821 --> 00:56:48.738
-Let's start bagging.
-(monitor beeping rapidly)

1132
00:56:48.863 --> 00:56:50.031
Make sure you secure the airway.

1133
00:56:50.240 --> 00:56:52.867
-(air pumping)
-High 80s. Keep going.

1134
00:56:52.909 --> 00:56:54.911
Get away!

1135
00:56:55.036 --> 00:56:57.163
-(breathing heavily)
-(beeping slows)

1136
00:57:00.291 --> 00:57:02.085
Jane.

1137
00:57:03.086 --> 00:57:06.256
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1138
00:57:06.339 --> 00:57:08.800
It's dangerous.

1139
00:57:08.883 --> 00:57:12.262
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1140
00:57:13.179 --> 00:57:14.431
JANE:
Yes.

1141
00:57:14.597 --> 00:57:16.683
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1142
00:57:16.766 --> 00:57:19.686
No. No.

1143
00:57:22.522 --> 00:57:25.483
"Father. if you be willing.

1144
00:57:25.567 --> 00:57:28.611
"let this cup pass me by.

1145
00:57:28.736 --> 00:57:31.906
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1146
00:57:32.073 --> 00:57:34.534
And what did Christ say next?

1147
00:57:36.119 --> 00:57:38.580
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1148
00:57:39.581 --> 00:57:43.042
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1149
00:57:43.209 --> 00:57:45.044
and you'll act. Jane.

1150
00:57:45.211 --> 00:57:48.882
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1151
00:57:52.093 --> 00:57:53.887
Now look around the room.

1152
00:57:54.971 --> 00:57:56.431
Slowly.

1153
00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:01.144
Left to right.

1154
00:58:04.355 --> 00:58:05.815
Stop there.

1155
00:58:07.150 --> 00:58:08.735
Get up.

1156
00:58:12.530 --> 00:58:13.656
Walk to the counter.

1157
00:58:13.698 --> 00:58:15.825
♪ ♪

1158
00:58:21.581 --> 00:58:23.625
Pull out the chopping knife.

1159
00:58:30.715 --> 00:58:31.841
Give me your phone!

1160
00:58:31.966 --> 00:58:33.593
-Oh. shit! What?
-Give me your phone.

1161
00:58:33.718 --> 00:58:35.011
Jackson. come on. come on.
come on. give me your phone.

1162
00:58:35.178 --> 00:58:36.262
Give me your phone.
Give me your phone.

1163
00:58:36.346 --> 00:58:37.722
-Okay. hold on. hold on!
-Come on!

1164
00:58:37.847 --> 00:58:38.556
Why? So you can throw it
out the window again?

1165
00:58:38.598 --> 00:58:41.184
(phone ringing)

1166
00:58:41.351 --> 00:58:43.019
Hey. Hugo. why am I
the only one...

1167
00:58:43.144 --> 00:58:45.730
-Daniel Kellner.
-Oh. my God. Daniel Kellner.

1168
00:58:45.855 --> 00:58:47.315
MARGARET (over phone):
They know where you are.

1169
00:58:47.482 --> 00:58:48.733
They know. Do you understand?

1170
00:58:48.900 --> 00:58:49.817
Who is this?

1171
00:58:49.943 --> 00:58:51.569
Do not go back to the house.

1172
00:58:51.653 --> 00:58:53.905
Scan-Scanlon dove on Jane.

1173
00:58:54.030 --> 00:58:55.365
Does that mean anything to you?

1174
00:58:55.532 --> 00:58:57.283
-Okay. Give me your...
-Look. they found you.

1175
00:58:57.408 --> 00:58:59.160
I don't know who you are.
and I don't know who they are.

1176
00:58:59.285 --> 00:59:00.870
but they're gonna kill you.

1177
00:59:00.954 --> 00:59:02.205
-Give me the phone.
-They are gonna kill you both.

1178
00:59:02.413 --> 00:59:03.915
-Give me my phone!
-You need to leave.

1179
00:59:04.082 --> 00:59:05.250
Give me my phone. Maggie!
Give me my phone! Oh. my God!

1180
00:59:05.333 --> 00:59:07.252
I'm so done
with your crazy shit!

1181
00:59:07.460 --> 00:59:09.045
(line clicks)

1182
00:59:14.384 --> 00:59:16.553
(panting)

1183
00:59:19.347 --> 00:59:21.474
(vehicles approaching)

1184
00:59:31.609 --> 00:59:33.736
(Daniel breathing heavily)

1185
00:59:41.703 --> 00:59:43.580
(softly):
Okay. Okay.

1186
00:59:51.170 --> 00:59:54.173
(birds chirping)

1187
01:00:01.097 --> 01:00:03.224
(panting)

1188
01:00:21.826 --> 01:00:23.411
(vehicle door opens)

1189
01:00:23.494 --> 01:00:25.121
(grunts)

1190
01:00:26.581 --> 01:00:28.458
(vehicle door closes)

1191
01:00:44.057 --> 01:00:46.142
(indistinct chatter)

1192
01:00:48.353 --> 01:00:49.979
(car door opens)

1193
01:00:58.363 --> 01:00:59.947
Okay.

1194
01:01:01.908 --> 01:01:03.451
(engine starts)

1195
01:01:03.576 --> 01:01:05.161
What am I doing?
What am I doing?

1196
01:01:05.328 --> 01:01:07.538
What am I doing?
What am I doing? Okay.

1197
01:01:07.664 --> 01:01:08.998
What am I doing?
What am I doing?

1198
01:01:09.123 --> 01:01:10.833
-What am I doing?
What am I doing? -Hold it!

1199
01:01:10.958 --> 01:01:12.543
-What am I doing? What am I
doing? What am I doing? -Stop!

1200
01:01:12.752 --> 01:01:13.795
-Hey! He's in the car! -Watch
out. watch out. watch out!

1201
01:01:14.003 --> 01:01:16.422
-What am I doing?
-(engine revving)

1202
01:01:16.589 --> 01:01:18.257
AGENT:
Shoot the tires!

1203
01:01:18.424 --> 01:01:19.550
It's him! It's him!

1204
01:01:19.717 --> 01:01:21.094
Watch out!

1205
01:01:21.219 --> 01:01:22.929
(indistinct shouting)

1206
01:01:23.012 --> 01:01:25.598
(gunfire)

1207
01:01:26.557 --> 01:01:28.267
AGENT:
Go for the tires!

1208
01:01:30.019 --> 01:01:32.939
(panting)

1209
01:01:34.357 --> 01:01:36.109
Oh. shit.

1210
01:01:36.943 --> 01:01:39.445
(engines revving in distance)

1211
01:01:47.453 --> 01:01:49.664
(tires squealing)

1212
01:01:53.209 --> 01:01:54.711
What am I doing?
What am I doing?

1213
01:01:54.877 --> 01:01:57.046
What am I doing?
What am I doing? What am I...

1214
01:01:57.130 --> 01:01:58.965
What am I doing?

1215
01:02:03.136 --> 01:02:04.345
-Hands up!
-Stop!

1216
01:02:04.429 --> 01:02:05.555
Get him!

1217
01:02:05.638 --> 01:02:06.889
Get out! Now!

1218
01:02:07.014 --> 01:02:07.849
-Get out of the car!
-(engine revving)

1219
01:02:08.015 --> 01:02:09.350
Let me see your hands! Hands up!

1220
01:02:09.559 --> 01:02:11.227
-Hands up!
-(tires squealing)

1221
01:02:23.781 --> 01:02:25.908
♪ ♪

1222
01:02:27.827 --> 01:02:29.912
(breathing heavily)

1223
01:02:41.507 --> 01:02:43.885
(engines revving)

1224
01:02:44.677 --> 01:02:46.387
(Daniel grunts)

1225
01:02:47.722 --> 01:02:49.265
Get your seat belt on!

1226
01:02:59.984 --> 01:03:01.068
Jane!

1227
01:03:01.986 --> 01:03:03.404
Jane.

1228
01:03:04.697 --> 01:03:06.282
(engines revving)

1229
01:03:13.873 --> 01:03:16.626
(breathing heavily)

1230
01:03:18.878 --> 01:03:19.879
(whimpering)

1231
01:03:20.087 --> 01:03:21.506
(heavy. shaky breathing)

1232
01:03:21.547 --> 01:03:22.965
(straining)

1233
01:03:23.090 --> 01:03:24.050
(grunts)

1234
01:03:24.091 --> 01:03:26.469
(whimpering. straining)

1235
01:03:28.471 --> 01:03:30.640
-(screams)
-(cries out in pain)

1236
01:03:30.723 --> 01:03:32.683
(breathing heavily)

1237
01:03:32.892 --> 01:03:35.228
(indistinct chatter)

1238
01:03:35.353 --> 01:03:37.188
-He's seizing. Stretch him out.
-Watch his head.

1239
01:03:37.313 --> 01:03:38.314
-Watch his head.
-I need a bite block.

1240
01:03:38.523 --> 01:03:40.650
♪ ♪

1241
01:03:45.279 --> 01:03:46.489
(grunts)

1242
01:03:50.326 --> 01:03:51.577
(gun fires)

1243
01:03:51.661 --> 01:03:52.912
Get down!

1244
01:03:57.792 --> 01:03:59.710
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!

1245
01:03:59.836 --> 01:04:01.212
(tires squealing)

1246
01:04:01.337 --> 01:04:02.421
(gasps)

1247
01:04:07.677 --> 01:04:10.263
No. no. no. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no. no.

1248
01:04:10.429 --> 01:04:11.806
No. no. no. no. no.

1249
01:04:11.889 --> 01:04:13.724
Look. Jane. it wasn't you.
It wasn't you.

1250
01:04:13.850 --> 01:04:15.101
It was Scanlon.

1251
01:04:15.268 --> 01:04:16.519
The device. The device.

1252
01:04:16.644 --> 01:04:19.021
Roll him on three.
One. two. three. go.

1253
01:04:24.443 --> 01:04:26.195
What the hell just happened?

1254
01:04:31.868 --> 01:04:33.119
-Secure the device!
-I got it. I got it.

1255
01:04:33.286 --> 01:04:34.495
I'm gloved. I'm gloved.

1256
01:04:41.627 --> 01:04:43.671
(tires squeal)

1257
01:04:47.592 --> 01:04:49.886
(engine revving)

1258
01:04:52.096 --> 01:04:54.181
Look behind us!
Tell me what you see!

1259
01:05:00.479 --> 01:05:03.232
Dust. I see dust.

1260
01:05:04.734 --> 01:05:06.986
They're coming! They're coming!

1261
01:05:08.029 --> 01:05:09.906
Stop. stop. stop. stop!

1262
01:05:09.989 --> 01:05:11.908
(tires squealing)

1263
01:05:11.949 --> 01:05:14.327
(rocks clattering)

1264
01:05:18.748 --> 01:05:20.833
(panting)

1265
01:05:31.636 --> 01:05:33.095
Run!

1266
01:05:34.013 --> 01:05:35.514
JANE:
Wait!

1267
01:05:37.058 --> 01:05:39.435
-What are you doing?
-Put it in drive!

1268
01:05:59.538 --> 01:06:01.582
(urgent chatter)

1269
01:06:01.624 --> 01:06:03.459
-You see them?
-You got a visual?

1270
01:06:03.542 --> 01:06:05.127
-Anybody got eyes on anything?
-They must have gone over.

1271
01:06:05.169 --> 01:06:06.671
Requesting underwater search
and recovery

1272
01:06:06.879 --> 01:06:08.130
-on site right now.
-They're down. They're down.

1273
01:06:08.255 --> 01:06:09.882
They're down.
They're in the water.

1274
01:06:10.049 --> 01:06:11.175
Can we get a team down there
and see if we can find them?

1275
01:06:11.258 --> 01:06:12.760
-We need some divers.
-Down there.

1276
01:06:12.927 --> 01:06:15.012
(chatter continues indistinctly)

1277
01:06:15.137 --> 01:06:17.139
(horns honking)

1278
01:06:17.181 --> 01:06:19.392
(panicked chatter)

1279
01:06:36.033 --> 01:06:37.660
They all think
the world's going to hell.

1280
01:06:37.827 --> 01:06:39.286
Got to get going now.
Jackson. okay?

1281
01:06:39.453 --> 01:06:40.663
Daniel Kellner's gonna be there.

1282
01:06:40.788 --> 01:06:42.206
Not right now.
but he will be soon.

1283
01:06:42.415 --> 01:06:43.874
-We got to go north.
-No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1284
01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:45.584
-Got to go north right now.
-No. we need to...

1285
01:06:45.710 --> 01:06:47.211
-We need to go back to the
hospital. -No. no. no. Jack.

1286
01:06:47.336 --> 01:06:48.629
This is not something you
get treated for. It's not...

1287
01:06:48.838 --> 01:06:50.256
You know what's wrong with you.

1288
01:06:50.381 --> 01:06:52.091
is that you think there's
something wrong with me.

1289
01:06:52.174 --> 01:06:54.135
Look at me. Look at me.

1290
01:06:55.970 --> 01:06:57.847
If I moved. you'd stay.

1291
01:06:59.015 --> 01:07:00.349
-What?
-Kansas City.

1292
01:07:00.474 --> 01:07:02.643
You want me to move.
You're gonna stay.

1293
01:07:22.705 --> 01:07:24.165
(sighs)

1294
01:07:24.206 --> 01:07:27.043
You know. this thing
that's happening. it's...

1295
01:07:27.126 --> 01:07:28.919
(takes deep breath)

1296
01:07:29.003 --> 01:07:30.337
It's not coming from me.

1297
01:07:30.463 --> 01:07:32.965
It's like I'm just a passenger.

1298
01:07:33.132 --> 01:07:34.508
That's not a bad thing.

1299
01:07:34.633 --> 01:07:37.053
It's. like. a really good thing.

1300
01:07:38.012 --> 01:07:39.847
-It's like your music.
-Uh-huh.

1301
01:07:39.972 --> 01:07:42.224
You know when you're
in the flow?

1302
01:07:42.308 --> 01:07:44.518
And it just feels...

1303
01:07:46.312 --> 01:07:48.064
I'm in the flow.

1304
01:07:48.189 --> 01:07:49.231
Okay.

1305
01:07:49.315 --> 01:07:50.691
And I told you I'd tell you

1306
01:07:50.775 --> 01:07:54.111
when I get where
I'm supposed to be. and...

1307
01:07:54.236 --> 01:07:55.780
this is it.

1308
01:07:55.863 --> 01:07:57.865
-Okay.
-Right here.

1309
01:07:57.948 --> 01:08:00.659
-It's where I'm supposed to be.
-Okay.

1310
01:08:00.743 --> 01:08:03.662
S-So...

1311
01:08:03.704 --> 01:08:08.584
we need to go north because
that's where Daniel Kellner is?

1312
01:08:08.709 --> 01:08:10.711
Sorry. No. He's east.

1313
01:08:10.753 --> 01:08:12.296
-Oh. And...
-He's east now.

1314
01:08:12.421 --> 01:08:14.090
How do you know that it's east?

1315
01:08:14.173 --> 01:08:17.343
It's just. I have
this vague inclination.

1316
01:08:17.468 --> 01:08:19.011
But he's east now.
He's somewhere east.

1317
01:08:19.220 --> 01:08:21.889
And where is "somewhere"?

1318
01:08:23.724 --> 01:08:25.559
You want me to drive?

1319
01:08:27.186 --> 01:08:28.854
I need a water.

1320
01:08:35.861 --> 01:08:37.363
(entry bell jingling)

1321
01:08:42.451 --> 01:08:43.661
Hey.

1322
01:08:43.828 --> 01:08:45.746
Hello. Hi.

1323
01:08:46.622 --> 01:08:48.791
Hi. Um...

1324
01:08:51.043 --> 01:08:52.545
Will you do me a favor?

1325
01:08:52.628 --> 01:08:54.338
-Dr. Coleman?
-(lively chatter)

1326
01:08:54.421 --> 01:08:56.549
Uh. uh. yes. yes. Thank you.
thank you for taking the call.

1327
01:08:56.674 --> 01:08:58.384
Uh. I-I don't know.

1328
01:08:58.551 --> 01:09:02.346
She just took off. and y-y-yes.
it's getting worse. much worse.

1329
01:09:02.429 --> 01:09:03.722
Yes. please. Thank you.

1330
01:09:03.889 --> 01:09:05.015
Yes. Hold on one second.

1331
01:09:05.057 --> 01:09:06.308
Excuse me. sir.

1332
01:09:06.475 --> 01:09:07.852
Do you know the address
around here?

1333
01:09:07.935 --> 01:09:10.146
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1334
01:09:11.105 --> 01:09:14.066
37 Pearl Street. Decatur.

1335
01:09:14.275 --> 01:09:16.068
We'll be here. Thank you.

1336
01:09:16.110 --> 01:09:17.653
(entry bell jingling)

1337
01:09:26.912 --> 01:09:28.664
BOY:
Hey. mister.

1338
01:09:29.582 --> 01:09:33.419
She said to say she loves you.
but she's going east.

1339
01:09:49.435 --> 01:09:50.978
Why Kansas City?

1340
01:09:51.061 --> 01:09:54.148
Best to focus on
getting you there tomorrow.

1341
01:09:54.315 --> 01:09:56.775
DANIEL (panting):
Hugo. I'm...

1342
01:09:58.444 --> 01:10:00.154
Uh. it's coming back to me.

1343
01:10:00.279 --> 01:10:02.072
Things are coming back to me.

1344
01:10:02.198 --> 01:10:03.490
What things?

1345
01:10:03.574 --> 01:10:05.201
Animals.

1346
01:10:05.409 --> 01:10:08.704
Friendly. terrifying animals
looking at me.

1347
01:10:10.289 --> 01:10:13.334
And you can't look away
no matter how hard you try?

1348
01:10:13.417 --> 01:10:16.128
No. no.
They have to look away first.

1349
01:10:18.797 --> 01:10:21.550
Is this a memory or a dream?

1350
01:10:22.509 --> 01:10:24.136
I can't tell anymore.

1351
01:10:24.261 --> 01:10:26.513
(shower water running)

1352
01:10:28.432 --> 01:10:30.142
HUGO:
Daniel?

1353
01:10:32.061 --> 01:10:33.687
Daniel.

1354
01:10:34.563 --> 01:10:36.065
Daniel.

1355
01:10:36.106 --> 01:10:38.317
It wasn't your idea
to recruit me. was it?

1356
01:10:38.442 --> 01:10:41.862
Not just for this but-but
to WARDEX in the first place.

1357
01:10:44.490 --> 01:10:45.991
No. it wasn't.

1358
01:10:46.158 --> 01:10:48.494
And there was a reason?

1359
01:10:48.535 --> 01:10:50.913
A specific reason
why you wanted me?

1360
01:10:52.456 --> 01:10:55.751
Other than your prodigious gift
for numbers? Yes.

1361
01:10:56.794 --> 01:10:59.630
You decided to keep
all of this to yourself?

1362
01:10:59.713 --> 01:11:02.716
Because I care about you.

1363
01:11:02.883 --> 01:11:04.718
Because you have a job to do.

1364
01:11:04.802 --> 01:11:08.430
And nothing can get
in the way of that.

1365
01:11:11.141 --> 01:11:13.227
There's parts of me...

1366
01:11:15.104 --> 01:11:18.315
...from when I was a kid
that I should be able to know.

1367
01:11:18.482 --> 01:11:20.192
and I don't.

1368
01:11:23.654 --> 01:11:25.281
They're just gone.

1369
01:11:26.240 --> 01:11:28.284
I'm so scared.

1370
01:11:29.576 --> 01:11:31.495
You don't need to be.

1371
01:11:31.578 --> 01:11:34.373
You have me and someone else.

1372
01:11:34.498 --> 01:11:38.294
And when the time is right.
everything will become clear.

1373
01:11:38.502 --> 01:11:41.046
Daniel. there's a place
you'll need to be

1374
01:11:41.213 --> 01:11:43.090
in the morning without fail.

1375
01:11:43.173 --> 01:11:46.093
There will be no other day
like tomorrow.

1376
01:11:48.887 --> 01:11:51.390
Where do you need me to go?

1377
01:11:53.517 --> 01:11:55.519
KCXE?

1378
01:11:55.728 --> 01:11:57.563
What's KCXE?

1379
01:12:38.312 --> 01:12:40.314
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1380
01:12:40.397 --> 01:12:42.149
(Margaret speaking indistinctly
on video)

1381
01:12:42.316 --> 01:12:44.193
I want you first
to look at this.

1382
01:12:45.235 --> 01:12:47.654
(Margaret speaking
unintelligibly on video)

1383
01:12:48.781 --> 01:12:50.532
Do you understand
what she's saying?

1384
01:12:51.658 --> 01:12:53.452
I hear her. It-it's gibberish.

1385
01:12:53.619 --> 01:12:55.037
I can't understand it.

1386
01:12:55.204 --> 01:12:58.916
Okay. I-I just heard this
for the first time.

1387
01:12:59.083 --> 01:13:00.417
and I can.

1388
01:13:00.501 --> 01:13:02.002
-It's English.
-English?

1389
01:13:02.127 --> 01:13:04.254
I mean. it's-it's math
turned English in my head.

1390
01:13:04.338 --> 01:13:06.006
translated into words.

1391
01:13:06.882 --> 01:13:10.302
When I look at this.
I hear this.

1392
01:13:10.386 --> 01:13:13.389
(Margaret clicking tongue
on video)

1393
01:13:14.848 --> 01:13:17.226
Danny. I'm gonna ask you
to do something.

1394
01:13:26.151 --> 01:13:27.903
You can't trust me anymore.

1395
01:13:31.198 --> 01:13:33.367
-(insects chirping)
-(sign creaking)

1396
01:13:46.839 --> 01:13:48.340
(gasps softly)

1397
01:13:49.842 --> 01:13:51.218
(hisses in pain)

1398
01:13:51.260 --> 01:13:53.554
(sighs)

1399
01:13:53.637 --> 01:13:55.597
(whimpers)

1400
01:14:01.728 --> 01:14:03.856
♪ ♪

1401
01:14:23.500 --> 01:14:25.627
♪ ♪

1402
01:14:40.225 --> 01:14:42.144
-(breathing heavily)
-(monitor beeping steadily)

1403
01:14:42.269 --> 01:14:44.062
Got him.

1404
01:14:46.273 --> 01:14:48.317
(groans)

1405
01:14:52.779 --> 01:14:54.823
(engine revving)

1406
01:15:12.257 --> 01:15:14.676
(engines revving)

1407
01:15:22.935 --> 01:15:24.853
(tires squealing)

1408
01:15:26.104 --> 01:15:28.190
(Daniel gasping)

1409
01:15:30.567 --> 01:15:33.028
(urgent chatter)

1410
01:15:35.697 --> 01:15:37.115
-They're here.
-(gasps)

1411
01:15:37.157 --> 01:15:38.492
-They're here.
-What?

1412
01:15:38.617 --> 01:15:40.786
-Take that end.
-Go. go. go.

1413
01:15:40.869 --> 01:15:42.996
(panting)

1414
01:15:44.248 --> 01:15:47.042
-The backpack. The backpack!
-You first.

1415
01:15:50.420 --> 01:15:52.548
(urgent chatter continues)

1416
01:15:59.513 --> 01:16:00.639
Come on.

1417
01:16:00.764 --> 01:16:02.975
This is all I've got.

1418
01:16:03.141 --> 01:16:04.518
You're coming. right?

1419
01:16:04.643 --> 01:16:05.936
-(banging at door)
-Shit.

1420
01:16:05.978 --> 01:16:07.229
Breach! Here!

1421
01:16:08.188 --> 01:16:09.815
(urgent chatter)

1422
01:16:09.940 --> 01:16:10.983
-No. come on. come on. come on.
-You got to take this.

1423
01:16:11.191 --> 01:16:12.776
(urgent chatter continues)

1424
01:16:12.985 --> 01:16:15.988
And for God's sake. Jane.
don't touch what's inside.

1425
01:16:16.071 --> 01:16:17.114
Go. Go.

1426
01:16:17.197 --> 01:16:19.324
(urgent chatter continues)

1427
01:16:23.078 --> 01:16:25.581
-(grunting)
-Get out of there!

1428
01:16:31.962 --> 01:16:33.755
Get on the ground!

1429
01:16:36.508 --> 01:16:38.218
They're burned.

1430
01:16:40.971 --> 01:16:42.431
(breathing heavily)

1431
01:16:42.639 --> 01:16:44.766
(agents shouting indistinctly
in distance)

1432
01:16:54.359 --> 01:16:56.111
It's not here.

1433
01:17:00.866 --> 01:17:02.451
Where's the device?

1434
01:17:07.623 --> 01:17:09.166
(sighs)

1435
01:17:09.249 --> 01:17:11.376
(jet engine whirring)

1436
01:17:19.092 --> 01:17:21.261
♪ ♪

1437
01:17:43.617 --> 01:17:44.993
SCANLON:
You've been misled. Daniel.

1438
01:17:45.160 --> 01:17:47.746
We can talk another time
about how hurtful

1439
01:17:47.913 --> 01:17:49.331
all this has been to me.

1440
01:17:49.414 --> 01:17:51.917
but here we are.

1441
01:17:52.084 --> 01:17:53.669
The archive's safe.

1442
01:17:53.877 --> 01:17:56.171
And now you're going
to tell me the name

1443
01:17:56.296 --> 01:17:58.006
of every confederate at WARDEX

1444
01:17:58.173 --> 01:18:00.676
and what exactly
Hugo's operation is planning.

1445
01:18:01.718 --> 01:18:04.846
But first.
without all this nonsense...

1446
01:18:07.724 --> 01:18:10.477
...you're going to tell me
what you did with the device.

1447
01:18:13.605 --> 01:18:15.857
(tires squealing)

1448
01:18:16.817 --> 01:18:18.944
♪ ♪

1449
01:18:29.621 --> 01:18:31.289
(tires squeal)

1450
01:18:33.583 --> 01:18:35.836
The hell do you think
you're doing driving like that?

1451
01:18:35.961 --> 01:18:38.380
You are Agent Thomas Farley.

1452
01:18:38.422 --> 01:18:41.633
Your ten-digit I.D. code is
3893398887.

1453
01:18:41.800 --> 01:18:43.844
What's the day code?

1454
01:18:44.970 --> 01:18:46.680
Kentucky filly.

1455
01:18:49.141 --> 01:18:51.143
(tires squealing)

1456
01:19:01.361 --> 01:19:02.988
-Agent Grady?
-Yes. ma'am.

1457
01:19:03.113 --> 01:19:04.698
Kentucky filly.
Mr. Scanlon sent for me.

1458
01:19:04.781 --> 01:19:06.241
Follow me.

1459
01:19:10.120 --> 01:19:11.872
(engine shuts off)

1460
01:19:11.955 --> 01:19:14.082
♪ ♪

1461
01:19:32.726 --> 01:19:34.853
♪ ♪

1462
01:19:51.328 --> 01:19:52.621
You're her.

1463
01:19:59.044 --> 01:20:01.421
Margaret Fairchild.

1464
01:20:20.857 --> 01:20:22.442
Jocelyn.

1465
01:20:28.198 --> 01:20:29.741
Jocelyn.

1466
01:20:36.832 --> 01:20:38.375
(gasps)

1467
01:20:38.500 --> 01:20:39.709
(grunting)

1468
01:20:39.876 --> 01:20:40.877
Leave her!

1469
01:20:41.086 --> 01:20:42.629
Stand down.

1470
01:21:00.605 --> 01:21:02.941
I know you.

1471
01:21:13.785 --> 01:21:16.079
I know you. too.

1472
01:21:16.204 --> 01:21:17.998
There's two coming out.

1473
01:21:18.123 --> 01:21:19.833
Don't allow them off the base.

1474
01:21:22.961 --> 01:21:25.589
Hey. Hey. Hey. back inside.

1475
01:21:25.714 --> 01:21:27.299
MARGARET: I've waited
too long to tell you.

1476
01:21:27.507 --> 01:21:29.050
and now it's too late.

1477
01:21:30.135 --> 01:21:33.054
But I loved you like my own son.

1478
01:21:36.391 --> 01:21:38.476
Stop. Stop. Stop.

1479
01:21:39.394 --> 01:21:41.062
They said we could go up
to the lake on Friday.

1480
01:21:41.187 --> 01:21:42.939
and-and Grandma and Grandpa
will be there.

1481
01:21:43.106 --> 01:21:47.402
and-and Uncle Howard and Bobby
and Teresa and everybody.

1482
01:21:47.527 --> 01:21:49.654
♪ ♪

1483
01:21:59.539 --> 01:22:01.207
How do you know these people?

1484
01:22:01.291 --> 01:22:02.876
MARGARET:
I don't.

1485
01:22:03.001 --> 01:22:04.753
You were just talking to them.

1486
01:22:10.383 --> 01:22:12.010
I don't understand
what's happening.

1487
01:22:12.052 --> 01:22:13.929
MARGARET:
Just get in!

1488
01:22:20.268 --> 01:22:22.771
-What did you see?
-(engine starts)

1489
01:22:23.813 --> 01:22:25.774
My wife.

1490
01:22:30.111 --> 01:22:31.780
My God.

1491
01:22:32.822 --> 01:22:34.449
What is she?

1492
01:22:35.784 --> 01:22:37.452
Unstoppable.

1493
01:22:37.494 --> 01:22:39.871
♪ ♪

1494
01:22:42.457 --> 01:22:43.959
(beeping)

1495
01:22:49.172 --> 01:22:50.507
DANIEL:
Where are you taking us?

1496
01:22:50.590 --> 01:22:52.509
MARGARET:
Kansas City.

1497
01:22:52.592 --> 01:22:53.927
DANIEL:
Why there?

1498
01:22:54.052 --> 01:22:55.845
-I have to.
-You don't have to go so...

1499
01:22:56.054 --> 01:22:58.014
-Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
-Uh. you're enjoying this.

1500
01:22:58.098 --> 01:23:00.642
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1501
01:23:00.809 --> 01:23:02.644
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1502
01:23:02.852 --> 01:23:04.354
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1503
01:23:04.396 --> 01:23:05.814
the last few days. you know.

1504
01:23:05.939 --> 01:23:07.691
-How do you know that?
-I just know things.

1505
01:23:07.774 --> 01:23:09.401
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1506
01:23:09.442 --> 01:23:11.319
and now I-I know things.

1507
01:23:11.486 --> 01:23:12.654
Things I don't really
want to know.

1508
01:23:12.821 --> 01:23:13.989
and all the things
I do want to know.

1509
01:23:14.072 --> 01:23:15.323
I don't really know at all.

1510
01:23:15.490 --> 01:23:16.825
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1511
01:23:16.866 --> 01:23:18.576
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1512
01:23:18.660 --> 01:23:20.328
-That must have been so...
-Hey. hey!

1513
01:23:20.412 --> 01:23:22.080
-(tires squealing)
-MARGARET: You see what I mean?

1514
01:23:22.122 --> 01:23:24.290
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1515
01:23:24.416 --> 01:23:28.169
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1516
01:23:29.170 --> 01:23:31.840
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1517
01:23:31.965 --> 01:23:33.508
I see the things
that they've lived.

1518
01:23:33.675 --> 01:23:35.760
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1519
01:23:35.885 --> 01:23:37.178
You know. like-like...

1520
01:23:37.303 --> 01:23:38.680
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1521
01:23:38.847 --> 01:23:40.598
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1522
01:23:40.724 --> 01:23:42.142
-"Keep your eyes on the road!"
-Keep your eyes on the road!

1523
01:23:42.225 --> 01:23:43.893
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1524
01:23:44.019 --> 01:23:45.145
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1525
01:23:45.186 --> 01:23:46.521
-You're absolutely right.
-Jane?

1526
01:23:46.688 --> 01:23:49.315
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1527
01:23:49.399 --> 01:23:51.359
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1528
01:23:51.568 --> 01:23:52.944
(makes whooshing sound)
It was so strong.

1529
01:23:53.153 --> 01:23:54.654
I dropped right in on you

1530
01:23:54.779 --> 01:23:56.239
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1531
01:23:56.448 --> 01:23:58.116
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1532
01:23:58.158 --> 01:23:59.743
How long you been able
to do this?

1533
01:23:59.951 --> 01:24:01.077
Since yesterday.

1534
01:24:01.202 --> 01:24:02.829
Since the bird.

1535
01:24:02.996 --> 01:24:04.456
-What bird?
-This-this bird.

1536
01:24:04.497 --> 01:24:06.082
Flew in through my window.

1537
01:24:06.249 --> 01:24:08.043
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1538
01:24:08.084 --> 01:24:09.127
Was it a cardinal?

1539
01:24:09.294 --> 01:24:10.503
Holy sh... How the...

1540
01:24:10.670 --> 01:24:12.047
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1541
01:24:12.088 --> 01:24:15.050
-(tires squealing)
-(crossing bell dinging)

1542
01:24:18.136 --> 01:24:19.471
I was 20. I was in college.

1543
01:24:19.596 --> 01:24:21.431
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1544
01:24:21.473 --> 01:24:22.891
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1545
01:24:23.016 --> 01:24:24.184
You were. but it was
the partying.

1546
01:24:24.350 --> 01:24:25.351
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1547
01:24:25.518 --> 01:24:26.936
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1548
01:24:27.103 --> 01:24:28.188
-Could you please stop?
-Sorry. I'm stopping.

1549
01:24:28.354 --> 01:24:29.606
-I was 20. I was in college.
-Yes.

1550
01:24:29.689 --> 01:24:32.233
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1551
01:24:32.400 --> 01:24:34.694
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1552
01:24:34.819 --> 01:24:36.237
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1553
01:24:36.404 --> 01:24:37.739
-It was a cardinal.
-In the window.

1554
01:24:37.906 --> 01:24:39.657
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1555
01:24:39.866 --> 01:24:41.326
everything just changed.

1556
01:24:41.451 --> 01:24:43.745
I saw things:
context. patterns. artifacting.

1557
01:24:43.828 --> 01:24:45.455
I could see it all.

1558
01:24:45.580 --> 01:24:47.373
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1559
01:24:47.540 --> 01:24:48.958
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1560
01:24:49.042 --> 01:24:50.460
Exactly. Solved equations

1561
01:24:50.585 --> 01:24:51.920
-without even thinking...
-And you could read

1562
01:24:52.045 --> 01:24:53.296
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1563
01:24:53.421 --> 01:24:54.464
-like it was nothing.
-Yeah.

1564
01:24:54.589 --> 01:24:55.590
How do you know all this?

1565
01:24:55.673 --> 01:24:57.258
I don't. You do.

1566
01:24:57.300 --> 01:24:58.468
God. you hated it.

1567
01:24:58.551 --> 01:25:00.303
-It was a curse.
-Yeah.

1568
01:25:00.386 --> 01:25:02.013
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1569
01:25:02.180 --> 01:25:03.973
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1570
01:25:04.099 --> 01:25:05.600
-to be around people.
-(train horn blaring)

1571
01:25:05.683 --> 01:25:07.435
Until you met Jane.

1572
01:25:08.770 --> 01:25:10.772
-(train horn continues blaring)
-(bell clanging)

1573
01:25:10.897 --> 01:25:12.440
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1574
01:25:12.565 --> 01:25:14.192
-What?
-That's what you said on TV.

1575
01:25:14.275 --> 01:25:15.693
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1576
01:25:15.902 --> 01:25:17.195
I understood every word.

1577
01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:18.947
What happened to us?

1578
01:25:19.072 --> 01:25:20.907
-(Daniel grunts)
-(gasps) Oh. my God.

1579
01:25:21.032 --> 01:25:22.992
-(tires squealing)
-(both grunting)

1580
01:25:23.201 --> 01:25:24.536
Who is it?!

1581
01:25:27.163 --> 01:25:28.289
Boyd. stop!

1582
01:25:28.414 --> 01:25:29.624
Boyd!

1583
01:25:31.918 --> 01:25:33.795
(engine revving)

1584
01:25:34.003 --> 01:25:35.755
(grunts)

1585
01:25:38.842 --> 01:25:39.926
Shit.

1586
01:25:40.927 --> 01:25:42.428
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1587
01:25:42.595 --> 01:25:44.556
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1588
01:25:48.601 --> 01:25:50.478
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1589
01:25:52.564 --> 01:25:53.815
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1590
01:25:56.109 --> 01:25:57.819
He's backing up! Get out now!

1591
01:26:08.246 --> 01:26:10.331
(both grunting)

1592
01:26:11.499 --> 01:26:13.293
-(Margaret screaming)
-All right. all right!

1593
01:26:21.718 --> 01:26:23.303
Get to the ladder!

1594
01:26:29.184 --> 01:26:31.102
MARGARET:
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1595
01:26:31.227 --> 01:26:32.478
DANIEL:
Okay.

1596
01:26:32.687 --> 01:26:34.480
(train horn blasting
in distance)

1597
01:26:38.651 --> 01:26:40.570
(horn continues blasting)

1598
01:26:40.612 --> 01:26:42.989
(both grunting)

1599
01:26:51.998 --> 01:26:54.292
-(bullets ricocheting)
-(grunting)

1600
01:26:56.961 --> 01:26:58.588
(gasping. whimpering)

1601
01:26:58.671 --> 01:27:01.007
-(horn honking)
-(tires squealing)

1602
01:27:07.263 --> 01:27:08.306
(train horn blaring)

1603
01:27:08.389 --> 01:27:10.475
Go! Jump!

1604
01:27:10.600 --> 01:27:12.477
(metallic creaking)

1605
01:27:13.895 --> 01:27:15.855
(gasps)

1606
01:27:18.316 --> 01:27:20.902
(horn blasting)

1607
01:27:23.363 --> 01:27:25.156
You got to jump!

1608
01:27:26.074 --> 01:27:27.575
Jump! Now!

1609
01:27:32.830 --> 01:27:35.667
-(Daniel straining)
-(breathing heavily)

1610
01:27:37.460 --> 01:27:39.337
(muffled shouting)

1611
01:27:49.639 --> 01:27:52.183
(grunting)

1612
01:27:53.893 --> 01:27:56.271
(heavy. gasping breaths)

1613
01:28:02.193 --> 01:28:03.611
Oh. my God.

1614
01:28:07.407 --> 01:28:10.618
(piano strings resonating)

1615
01:28:11.703 --> 01:28:14.539
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1616
01:28:15.373 --> 01:28:16.874
I can't breathe.

1617
01:28:18.167 --> 01:28:20.295
-It's okay. It's okay.
-I can't breathe.

1618
01:28:20.420 --> 01:28:22.005
-I think you're having
a panic attack. -Oh. my God.

1619
01:28:22.130 --> 01:28:24.173
-It's okay. It's okay.
-Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1620
01:28:24.340 --> 01:28:26.050
-It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
-(stammers) My hands.

1621
01:28:26.134 --> 01:28:27.885
-We're okay.
-It's like my dad.

1622
01:28:28.052 --> 01:28:29.512
-It's like my dad. My hands.
-No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1623
01:28:29.637 --> 01:28:31.472
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1624
01:28:31.639 --> 01:28:32.890
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1625
01:28:32.932 --> 01:28:34.475
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1626
01:28:34.559 --> 01:28:36.436
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1627
01:28:36.477 --> 01:28:37.979
-I can't control it.
-You can.

1628
01:28:38.104 --> 01:28:40.732
(sobbing): Oh. my God.
I ran away from him.

1629
01:28:40.898 --> 01:28:43.609
-I didn't want to be around
him anymore. -No. no. no. Stop.

1630
01:28:43.735 --> 01:28:45.486
-I want this gone!
-Okay.

1631
01:28:45.653 --> 01:28:48.406
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1632
01:28:48.531 --> 01:28:50.992
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1633
01:28:51.159 --> 01:28:53.077
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1634
01:28:53.202 --> 01:28:54.245
Give me your hands.

1635
01:28:54.329 --> 01:28:55.580
-Okay. look at me.
-No. no. no.

1636
01:28:55.621 --> 01:28:56.914
-Look at me.
-I-I'm gonna see things.

1637
01:28:56.998 --> 01:28:58.708
-I'm gonna see things. Please.
-Okay.

1638
01:28:58.750 --> 01:28:59.751
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1639
01:28:59.959 --> 01:29:01.336
(both taking deep breaths)

1640
01:29:01.461 --> 01:29:03.087
That's it. Okay.

1641
01:29:03.212 --> 01:29:05.131
I can't feel my hands.

1642
01:29:05.256 --> 01:29:07.091
Okay. Okay.

1643
01:29:07.216 --> 01:29:08.885
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1644
01:29:08.968 --> 01:29:10.636
-Come on. Put your hands there.
-(piano strings thrumming)

1645
01:29:10.803 --> 01:29:12.597
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1646
01:29:12.764 --> 01:29:14.390
I'm here. I'm here.

1647
01:29:14.515 --> 01:29:15.892
We're here.

1648
01:29:15.975 --> 01:29:17.643
-We're okay.
-Okay.

1649
01:29:18.770 --> 01:29:20.146
-We're okay.
-We're okay.

1650
01:29:20.271 --> 01:29:22.398
We're okay.

1651
01:29:22.440 --> 01:29:25.234
We're okay now. You're okay.

1652
01:29:25.276 --> 01:29:27.487
(heavy breathing continues)

1653
01:29:29.614 --> 01:29:31.657
We're okay.

1654
01:29:31.741 --> 01:29:33.034
Okay.

1655
01:29:33.159 --> 01:29:35.286
(breathing calms down)

1656
01:29:37.747 --> 01:29:39.624
Thank you.

1657
01:29:42.585 --> 01:29:44.921
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1658
01:29:45.004 --> 01:29:46.255
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1659
01:29:46.339 --> 01:29:48.466
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1660
01:29:49.467 --> 01:29:50.968
(Hugo grunts)

1661
01:29:51.052 --> 01:29:53.221
H-Hugo?

1662
01:29:53.346 --> 01:29:54.722
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1663
01:29:54.847 --> 01:29:56.224
for a minute. please?

1664
01:29:56.307 --> 01:29:59.143
-Now. please! Out!
-Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1665
01:29:59.227 --> 01:30:00.895
(sighs)

1666
01:30:03.356 --> 01:30:05.400
-(door opens)
-(groans)

1667
01:30:05.525 --> 01:30:07.193
SCANLON:
Hello. Hugo.

1668
01:30:08.277 --> 01:30:10.405
♪ ♪

1669
01:30:12.782 --> 01:30:14.951
Noah. please.

1670
01:30:15.952 --> 01:30:17.829
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1671
01:30:17.995 --> 01:30:19.747
It's not a magic wand.

1672
01:30:19.956 --> 01:30:21.749
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1673
01:30:21.833 --> 01:30:24.710
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1674
01:30:24.794 --> 01:30:29.298
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1675
01:30:29.382 --> 01:30:31.384
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1676
01:30:31.467 --> 01:30:33.678
Yes.

1677
01:30:33.761 --> 01:30:35.680
He was.

1678
01:30:37.432 --> 01:30:41.561
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1679
01:30:42.728 --> 01:30:44.564
Not in any way you'd understand.

1680
01:30:44.730 --> 01:30:46.274
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1681
01:30:46.357 --> 01:30:48.776
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1682
01:30:48.943 --> 01:30:51.404
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1683
01:30:51.529 --> 01:30:52.905
No. don't condescend to me.

1684
01:30:53.030 --> 01:30:54.407
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1685
01:30:54.490 --> 01:30:56.534
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1686
01:30:56.659 --> 01:30:58.119
From your friends?

1687
01:30:58.286 --> 01:30:59.829
Yes.

1688
01:30:59.871 --> 01:31:02.748
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1689
01:31:02.832 --> 01:31:05.418
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1690
01:31:05.501 --> 01:31:09.422
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1691
01:31:09.630 --> 01:31:11.757
Our rejection
of this understanding

1692
01:31:11.883 --> 01:31:14.010
is leading us to our extinction.

1693
01:31:15.052 --> 01:31:18.139
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1694
01:31:20.057 --> 01:31:21.559
Five years ago.

1695
01:31:21.767 --> 01:31:23.728
That was you. wasn't it?

1696
01:31:25.354 --> 01:31:26.731
Yes.

1697
01:31:27.773 --> 01:31:30.735
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1698
01:31:30.860 --> 01:31:33.112
how could you lie to me
for five years

1699
01:31:33.196 --> 01:31:34.822
every time you walked
through the door?

1700
01:31:34.906 --> 01:31:37.742
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1701
01:31:39.619 --> 01:31:42.788
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1702
01:31:42.955 --> 01:31:45.333
Around the time you lost yours.

1703
01:31:47.835 --> 01:31:49.420
When you lost her.

1704
01:31:53.674 --> 01:31:56.260
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1705
01:31:56.469 --> 01:31:57.720
Because you shut down.

1706
01:31:57.803 --> 01:31:59.138
Do not presume to know me.

1707
01:31:59.305 --> 01:32:00.640
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1708
01:32:00.806 --> 01:32:02.308
to need-to-know. including me.

1709
01:32:02.433 --> 01:32:03.643
Because you were very clear.

1710
01:32:03.768 --> 01:32:05.019
All you needed to know was them.

1711
01:32:05.186 --> 01:32:07.396
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1712
01:32:07.605 --> 01:32:10.107
They will be.

1713
01:32:10.274 --> 01:32:12.360
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1714
01:32:12.485 --> 01:32:14.153
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1715
01:32:14.278 --> 01:32:16.322
You don't need to fear them.

1716
01:32:17.240 --> 01:32:19.116
I fear us.

1717
01:32:19.325 --> 01:32:22.245
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1718
01:32:22.453 --> 01:32:26.541
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1719
01:32:26.707 --> 01:32:28.417
That truth will upend
all established order

1720
01:32:28.501 --> 01:32:29.669
across the entire world.

1721
01:32:29.835 --> 01:32:32.380
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1722
01:32:32.421 --> 01:32:36.634
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1723
01:32:36.717 --> 01:32:39.178
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1724
01:32:39.303 --> 01:32:40.555
Your own wealth and power--

1725
01:32:40.680 --> 01:32:42.348
that's all
you've been protecting.

1726
01:32:42.473 --> 01:32:45.226
Noah. Noah.

1727
01:32:45.351 --> 01:32:47.520
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1728
01:32:47.645 --> 01:32:50.940
and an equal need
to be believed.

1729
01:32:51.065 --> 01:32:53.150
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1730
01:32:53.276 --> 01:32:54.860
You've infantilized anyone

1731
01:32:54.944 --> 01:32:57.572
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1732
01:32:57.780 --> 01:33:00.575
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1733
01:33:00.616 --> 01:33:03.244
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1734
01:33:03.369 --> 01:33:05.079
and overridden them
for the crime

1735
01:33:05.162 --> 01:33:07.123
of simply being astonished.

1736
01:33:07.290 --> 01:33:10.042
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1737
01:33:10.167 --> 01:33:11.961
the chance to believe them. too.

1738
01:33:12.003 --> 01:33:14.589
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1739
01:33:14.755 --> 01:33:16.382
telling others
of their experiences.

1740
01:33:16.507 --> 01:33:18.759
They are starved for the truth.

1741
01:33:18.843 --> 01:33:22.388
This 79-year terror campaign

1742
01:33:22.471 --> 01:33:25.933
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1743
01:33:26.142 --> 01:33:27.977
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1744
01:33:28.102 --> 01:33:30.438
-HUGO: Get out! Get out!
-Sorry. sir. we have...

1745
01:33:30.521 --> 01:33:32.690
Turn around and get out now!

1746
01:33:38.029 --> 01:33:40.948
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1747
01:33:40.990 --> 01:33:43.951
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1748
01:33:44.076 --> 01:33:46.537
-Her.
-Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1749
01:33:46.662 --> 01:33:48.247
-Him.
-Nathan Twinning.

1750
01:33:48.331 --> 01:33:49.832
Hugo's chief aide.

1751
01:33:49.957 --> 01:33:51.417
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1752
01:33:51.500 --> 01:33:53.294
Hang on.

1753
01:33:56.213 --> 01:34:00.801
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1754
01:34:02.011 --> 01:34:03.721
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1755
01:34:03.929 --> 01:34:06.641
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1756
01:34:06.724 --> 01:34:08.893
(Scanlon breathing heavily)

1757
01:34:12.897 --> 01:34:15.232
(church bell tolling
in distance)

1758
01:34:15.358 --> 01:34:17.902
Sister Maura. Sister.

1759
01:34:20.071 --> 01:34:22.156
(indistinct whispering)

1760
01:34:26.035 --> 01:34:27.495
Jane?

1761
01:34:27.578 --> 01:34:29.080
Where are you. Jane?

1762
01:34:29.163 --> 01:34:30.915
-(quiet chatter)
-(bell dinging)

1763
01:34:31.916 --> 01:34:33.376
Does God love us?

1764
01:34:33.542 --> 01:34:36.587
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1765
01:34:36.712 --> 01:34:40.341
Does he love only us?

1766
01:34:40.424 --> 01:34:42.677
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1767
01:34:42.843 --> 01:34:45.554
but do you think
it's possible that...

1768
01:34:45.638 --> 01:34:47.181
SISTER MAURA:
On Earth.

1769
01:34:48.391 --> 01:34:49.517
What?

1770
01:34:49.725 --> 01:34:51.227
Genesis.

1771
01:34:51.352 --> 01:34:56.023
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1772
01:34:57.733 --> 01:34:59.443
(bell dinging)

1773
01:35:04.990 --> 01:35:07.201
Do you think
there could be others?

1774
01:35:08.786 --> 01:35:10.871
Yes.

1775
01:35:10.955 --> 01:35:12.540
I would think so.

1776
01:35:12.707 --> 01:35:16.293
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1777
01:35:16.419 --> 01:35:20.464
yet save it only for us?

1778
01:35:21.549 --> 01:35:26.554
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

1779
01:35:26.679 --> 01:35:30.349
if someone showed you.
proved it to you...

1780
01:35:32.143 --> 01:35:34.395
...would that frighten you?

1781
01:35:34.520 --> 01:35:37.273
SISTER MAURA:
No. Why? Should it?

1782
01:35:37.356 --> 01:35:40.609
But what if it all collapsed?

1783
01:35:40.651 --> 01:35:43.028
For you and every other person
of faith in the world.

1784
01:35:43.112 --> 01:35:44.238
Then what?

1785
01:35:44.280 --> 01:35:45.448
Oh.

1786
01:35:45.656 --> 01:35:47.867
My dear. Jane.

1787
01:35:47.992 --> 01:35:52.913
I don't think that you ever
doubted your belief in God.

1788
01:35:52.955 --> 01:35:56.041
I think you lost your faith
in people.

1789
01:36:00.463 --> 01:36:04.049
They say you're paying because
you borrowed their phone?

1790
01:36:11.223 --> 01:36:12.850
Are you near the computer?

1791
01:36:12.975 --> 01:36:14.477
SISTER MAURA:
Yes.

1792
01:36:14.643 --> 01:36:16.854
What is KCXE?

1793
01:36:16.979 --> 01:36:19.607
Just those letters-- KCXE.

1794
01:36:26.906 --> 01:36:28.783
Remember being a kid?

1795
01:36:28.991 --> 01:36:30.409
Sure.

1796
01:36:30.534 --> 01:36:32.953
Mostly stuff after I was ten.

1797
01:36:38.042 --> 01:36:42.129
Can you tell anything about me
from when I was small?

1798
01:36:46.759 --> 01:36:48.886
♪ ♪

1799
01:37:01.065 --> 01:37:03.150
It's just a fox.

1800
01:37:10.032 --> 01:37:13.118
(brakes squealing)

1801
01:37:16.580 --> 01:37:18.123
DANIEL:
No. no. no. No!

1802
01:37:18.249 --> 01:37:21.001
-Stop! Stop!
-No. Daniel!

1803
01:37:21.126 --> 01:37:22.920
-(indistinct chatter)
-(grunting)

1804
01:37:23.003 --> 01:37:24.380
-Let's go. Come with us.
-Hold on.

1805
01:37:24.463 --> 01:37:26.590
-Hold on.
-Let's go.

1806
01:37:26.674 --> 01:37:28.342
I know him. I know him.

1807
01:37:28.467 --> 01:37:29.844
We just got to check you
real quick.

1808
01:37:30.010 --> 01:37:32.429
make sure nobody's in there
with you.

1809
01:37:32.596 --> 01:37:34.181
(electronic trilling)

1810
01:37:38.727 --> 01:37:39.812
(electronic trilling)

1811
01:37:39.895 --> 01:37:41.397
Clear.

1812
01:37:41.480 --> 01:37:43.482
All right. let's load up.

1813
01:37:43.649 --> 01:37:45.276
See. the thing about
fire trucks--

1814
01:37:45.359 --> 01:37:47.695
everyone gets the hell
out of your way.

1815
01:37:47.903 --> 01:37:50.030
♪ ♪

1816
01:38:04.003 --> 01:38:05.880
(Daniel inhales deeply)

1817
01:38:08.340 --> 01:38:10.467
♪ ♪

1818
01:38:36.493 --> 01:38:38.245
I knew you'd make it.

1819
01:38:38.287 --> 01:38:39.788
I'm glad you knew.

1820
01:38:39.997 --> 01:38:41.665
Never a doubt.

1821
01:38:48.797 --> 01:38:50.507
DANIEL:
Margaret.

1822
01:38:52.092 --> 01:38:53.677
Margaret.

1823
01:38:56.513 --> 01:38:58.015
Hello. Margaret.

1824
01:39:00.142 --> 01:39:02.353
Do you know who I am?

1825
01:39:02.394 --> 01:39:03.938
Of course. You're Hugo.

1826
01:39:06.774 --> 01:39:08.359
Nathan.

1827
01:39:09.693 --> 01:39:13.155
Chloe. Malik.

1828
01:39:13.364 --> 01:39:15.950
Jordan. Letisha.

1829
01:39:17.076 --> 01:39:18.827
Grace.

1830
01:39:18.994 --> 01:39:20.663
Hi. Terri.

1831
01:39:20.746 --> 01:39:22.748
Kaitlyn. That's Everett.

1832
01:39:32.758 --> 01:39:34.927
♪ ♪

1833
01:39:50.275 --> 01:39:52.444
I think we got it mostly right.

1834
01:39:53.821 --> 01:39:55.239
Margaret.

1835
01:39:55.447 --> 01:39:57.992
Why won't you look at me?

1836
01:39:58.117 --> 01:39:59.535
Because you're-you're the guy.

1837
01:39:59.660 --> 01:40:01.912
You're the guy
who knows everything.

1838
01:40:03.497 --> 01:40:06.333
And I'm... and I'm not ready
to know everything.

1839
01:40:08.002 --> 01:40:11.547
Including. like. why-why my mom
and dad's entire goddamn house

1840
01:40:11.588 --> 01:40:13.007
is just sitting right there!

1841
01:40:13.048 --> 01:40:16.301
What is going on?
Why are you doing this?

1842
01:40:16.427 --> 01:40:18.387
That's where I grew up.
That's where I grew up.

1843
01:40:18.512 --> 01:40:21.682
This is my life.
This is my life.

1844
01:40:21.724 --> 01:40:23.976
And this matters--
what I want. who I am.

1845
01:40:24.018 --> 01:40:27.771
not who I am as you
or him or her. but as me.

1846
01:40:31.775 --> 01:40:33.777
No. no. no. no. no. no. no.

1847
01:40:33.861 --> 01:40:36.196
No. No.

1848
01:40:37.656 --> 01:40:40.451
I will not be anyone's religion.

1849
01:40:48.208 --> 01:40:50.627
(sobbing)

1850
01:40:53.255 --> 01:40:55.382
♪ ♪

1851
01:41:05.601 --> 01:41:07.728
♪ ♪

1852
01:41:23.660 --> 01:41:25.913
(whimpers softly)

1853
01:41:51.063 --> 01:41:52.564
My room.

1854
01:41:56.360 --> 01:41:58.278
Oh. my room.

1855
01:42:25.222 --> 01:42:27.724
Why would you build all of this?

1856
01:42:27.850 --> 01:42:30.310
To create a passage.

1857
01:42:32.271 --> 01:42:34.273
To return you to your experience

1858
01:42:34.481 --> 01:42:37.359
in the most familiar way
possible.

1859
01:42:37.442 --> 01:42:39.736
What experience?

1860
01:42:41.822 --> 01:42:44.158
The one you shared
with Margaret.

1861
01:42:45.826 --> 01:42:47.035
I shared?

1862
01:42:47.119 --> 01:42:49.329
I am not going back there.

1863
01:42:49.413 --> 01:42:51.206
-Hugo. -How much do you
remember about that night?

1864
01:42:51.331 --> 01:42:52.958
I don't remember.
and I don't want to remember.

1865
01:42:53.041 --> 01:42:54.751
and I don't want you
making me remember.

1866
01:42:54.835 --> 01:42:56.962
-Okay. Oh. my...
-HUGO: Wait. Wait.

1867
01:42:57.045 --> 01:42:58.755
Wait.

1868
01:42:58.964 --> 01:43:00.841
Everything that happened to you
on the 23rd of February. 1996.

1869
01:43:00.924 --> 01:43:02.467
-is blocked. -I don't want
to know anything about it.

1870
01:43:02.551 --> 01:43:03.927
The only way for you
to know what's next

1871
01:43:04.011 --> 01:43:05.596
is to understand
what came before.

1872
01:43:05.762 --> 01:43:07.014
I don't want to talk about it.
I don't. Stop. stop. stop.

1873
01:43:07.139 --> 01:43:08.557
And then you'll know
your purpose.

1874
01:43:08.682 --> 01:43:09.808
Please don't make me.
I don't want to hear it.

1875
01:43:09.933 --> 01:43:10.767
You won't be
a passenger anymore.

1876
01:43:10.893 --> 01:43:12.769
I told you no! (gasps)

1877
01:43:17.441 --> 01:43:20.819
You have the gift
but no control.

1878
01:43:20.944 --> 01:43:22.821
No understanding
of your purpose.

1879
01:43:22.988 --> 01:43:24.656
Not a clue as to
what your situation

1880
01:43:24.823 --> 01:43:27.034
will demand of you beyond today.

1881
01:43:27.159 --> 01:43:29.453
The only way for you
to acquire it

1882
01:43:29.536 --> 01:43:33.081
is to go back
to where it all began.

1883
01:43:33.207 --> 01:43:34.875
To go home.

1884
01:43:40.923 --> 01:43:45.010
And when you do. Margaret.
you'll know everything.

1885
01:43:45.093 --> 01:43:48.388
More than what was ever
humanly possible.

1886
01:44:09.618 --> 01:44:11.828
They gifted each of you.

1887
01:44:11.954 --> 01:44:14.873
Margaret. what was dormant
in you for most of your life

1888
01:44:15.040 --> 01:44:17.751
was activated only yesterday.

1889
01:44:18.710 --> 01:44:21.255
And yours. 15 years ago.

1890
01:44:21.463 --> 01:44:23.382
They gave you fluency
in the language

1891
01:44:23.423 --> 01:44:25.801
in which the book
of the universe is written:

1892
01:44:26.009 --> 01:44:27.678
mathematics.

1893
01:44:27.844 --> 01:44:31.306
Taught it to you. imbued it
so you could understand them.

1894
01:44:32.349 --> 01:44:36.520
And they imbued you
so you could understand us.

1895
01:44:38.689 --> 01:44:41.149
It's the two of you.

1896
01:44:41.275 --> 01:44:42.567
(chuckles)

1897
01:44:42.734 --> 01:44:46.446
It's always been
just the two of you.

1898
01:44:54.871 --> 01:44:57.040
(quiet. indistinct chatter)

1899
01:45:08.635 --> 01:45:10.178
You can direct it

1900
01:45:10.262 --> 01:45:12.639
or feel where it wants
to take you.

1901
01:45:13.807 --> 01:45:15.809
It can find
what you're looking for.

1902
01:45:15.934 --> 01:45:18.770
It'll be an instrument
of your will.

1903
01:45:18.854 --> 01:45:21.315
But you must give yourself
over to it.

1904
01:45:22.482 --> 01:45:24.985
I'll find out
what's happening to me.

1905
01:45:27.362 --> 01:45:28.739
What?

1906
01:45:28.905 --> 01:45:30.449
It's gonna be okay.

1907
01:45:30.532 --> 01:45:32.159
I promise.

1908
01:45:39.207 --> 01:45:41.335
♪ ♪

1909
01:45:49.301 --> 01:45:50.886
Whatever happens. Daniel.

1910
01:45:51.011 --> 01:45:53.096
-don't you let go.
-Don't you let go.

1911
01:45:56.183 --> 01:45:57.768
Margaret.

1912
01:46:00.145 --> 01:46:02.356
Look around the room
one more time.

1913
01:46:03.732 --> 01:46:05.859
♪ ♪

1914
01:46:09.237 --> 01:46:12.657
You're a ten-year-old girl
asleep in your bed.

1915
01:46:12.783 --> 01:46:14.701
Something woke you up.
didn't it?

1916
01:46:14.743 --> 01:46:15.952
Yes.

1917
01:46:16.119 --> 01:46:17.871
So what did you do?

1918
01:46:18.789 --> 01:46:20.999
I sang my song.

1919
01:46:23.001 --> 01:46:26.046
(humming
"Someday My Prince Will Come")

1920
01:46:36.306 --> 01:46:39.935
♪ And away to his castle ♪

1921
01:46:40.102 --> 01:46:42.479
♪ We'll go ♪

1922
01:46:42.604 --> 01:46:46.274
♪ To be happy forever ♪

1923
01:46:46.483 --> 01:46:49.069
♪ I know ♪

1924
01:46:49.194 --> 01:46:53.323
♪ And the birds will sing. ♪

1925
01:46:59.121 --> 01:47:01.248
♪ ♪

1926
01:47:03.667 --> 01:47:06.128
I can see them.

1927
01:47:06.169 --> 01:47:08.213
Right over there.

1928
01:47:08.380 --> 01:47:10.257
They're coming into the room.

1929
01:47:12.717 --> 01:47:14.845
♪ ♪

1930
01:47:16.680 --> 01:47:19.766
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1931
01:47:36.366 --> 01:47:37.784
(chitters softly)

1932
01:48:01.349 --> 01:48:03.477
♪ ♪

1933
01:48:06.396 --> 01:48:08.231
DANIEL:
No. no. no. don't go with them.

1934
01:48:08.398 --> 01:48:09.649
They're not animals.

1935
01:48:09.816 --> 01:48:11.818
Don't go with them.
They're not animals.

1936
01:48:11.902 --> 01:48:13.361
They're not animals!

1937
01:48:13.528 --> 01:48:15.155
-It's okay. It's okay.
-(panting) They're not.

1938
01:48:15.322 --> 01:48:19.242
They-they present as animals
to calm us.

1939
01:48:24.414 --> 01:48:27.000
When I walked through the glass.

1940
01:48:27.167 --> 01:48:31.171
it was like
this curtain of warm water.

1941
01:48:33.924 --> 01:48:36.259
And the snow...

1942
01:48:36.468 --> 01:48:39.763
was so warm on my feet.

1943
01:48:41.431 --> 01:48:44.309
(long. slow gasp)

1944
01:48:44.392 --> 01:48:46.478
The house.

1945
01:48:52.609 --> 01:48:55.320
"Hansel and Gretel."

1946
01:49:11.920 --> 01:49:14.047
(soft electrical warbling)

1947
01:49:20.345 --> 01:49:22.472
♪ ♪

1948
01:49:25.350 --> 01:49:27.394
(soft electrical warbling)

1949
01:49:30.647 --> 01:49:32.732
(soft whooshing)

1950
01:49:40.532 --> 01:49:42.117
(gruff. heavy breathing nearby)

1951
01:49:42.242 --> 01:49:44.869
(young Margaret
breathing heavily)

1952
01:49:57.299 --> 01:50:00.093
(chittering)

1953
01:50:10.729 --> 01:50:13.523
(rapid. gasping breaths)

1954
01:50:25.118 --> 01:50:26.786
Shh.

1955
01:50:32.584 --> 01:50:34.919
Hold my hand.

1956
01:50:43.803 --> 01:50:46.139
(young Daniel's breathing
slowing down)

1957
01:50:53.521 --> 01:50:55.649
♪ ♪

1958
01:50:58.401 --> 01:51:00.570
(trembling breaths)

1959
01:51:02.947 --> 01:51:05.158
-(soft electrical whooshing)
-(gasps)

1960
01:51:11.915 --> 01:51:14.000
(soft electrical crackling)

1961
01:51:27.097 --> 01:51:30.183
(soft whooshing. crackling)

1962
01:51:31.893 --> 01:51:34.020
-(sharp whoosh)
-(gasps)

1963
01:51:43.154 --> 01:51:45.323
♪ ♪

1964
01:51:48.118 --> 01:51:50.203
(soft whirring)

1965
01:51:53.623 --> 01:51:55.625
(soft whooshing)

1966
01:52:05.969 --> 01:52:08.054
(breathing heavily)

1967
01:52:11.599 --> 01:52:13.059
Whoa.

1968
01:52:14.936 --> 01:52:16.730
Whoa.

1969
01:52:33.455 --> 01:52:35.582
♪ ♪

1970
01:52:54.434 --> 01:52:56.269
Hello. Hugo.

1971
01:52:59.522 --> 01:53:01.858
It's so nice
to finally know you.

1972
01:53:02.776 --> 01:53:04.611
(tires squealing)

1973
01:53:04.736 --> 01:53:06.905
♪ ♪

1974
01:53:15.872 --> 01:53:18.041
(indistinct chatter)

1975
01:53:19.209 --> 01:53:20.794
They found us.

1976
01:53:20.877 --> 01:53:23.171
(labored breathing)

1977
01:53:23.296 --> 01:53:24.714
HUGO:
Are they out front or out back?

1978
01:53:24.923 --> 01:53:26.299
Most likely on all sides.

1979
01:53:26.508 --> 01:53:29.636
Okay. give me the. uh...
the-the-the thingy.

1980
01:53:29.677 --> 01:53:33.306
Thermal imaging showed
43 heat signatures inside here.

1981
01:53:33.473 --> 01:53:35.183
This whole area's
an industrial decay zone.

1982
01:53:35.225 --> 01:53:37.769
No other structure has
more than five people in it.

1983
01:53:39.270 --> 01:53:41.731
(heavy. labored breathing)

1984
01:53:45.193 --> 01:53:46.903
-(groans)
-Hey.

1985
01:53:47.070 --> 01:53:49.489
(grunts) Get on with it.

1986
01:53:54.202 --> 01:53:56.287
(whirring)

1987
01:54:05.797 --> 01:54:07.799
(electronic trilling. beeping)

1988
01:54:23.147 --> 01:54:25.275
♪ ♪

1989
01:54:33.658 --> 01:54:34.951
(hushed):
No one move.

1990
01:54:35.118 --> 01:54:37.328
No one make a sound.

1991
01:54:37.412 --> 01:54:38.997
They can't see us.

1992
01:54:42.458 --> 01:54:44.210
Give it to me.

1993
01:54:49.591 --> 01:54:51.509
This is not right.

1994
01:54:54.429 --> 01:54:58.224
They can't see us.
but they can see this.

1995
01:54:59.142 --> 01:55:01.769
We need to move now.

1996
01:55:01.895 --> 01:55:04.898
This is not gonna last long.
We got to go right now.

1997
01:55:15.199 --> 01:55:16.576
(hushed):
Look. They can't see me.

1998
01:55:16.659 --> 01:55:18.077
They can't see us. Let's go.

1999
01:55:18.161 --> 01:55:19.412
Quiet. quiet.

2000
01:55:19.621 --> 01:55:20.788
Through the back doors.
Any back door.

2001
01:55:20.914 --> 01:55:22.874
Go quiet. Go quiet.
Down the alley.

2002
01:55:22.916 --> 01:55:25.001
-Let's go. Let's go.
-Quiet.

2003
01:55:25.209 --> 01:55:27.962
Everybody. stop moving.

2004
01:55:28.087 --> 01:55:30.214
(rapid footsteps)

2005
01:55:36.137 --> 01:55:38.181
There. Look there.

2006
01:55:40.516 --> 01:55:42.101
Oh. God. I'm losing it.

2007
01:55:42.268 --> 01:55:43.937
I'm losing it.
You need to go faster.

2008
01:55:44.103 --> 01:55:45.730
-Get to the fire truck.
-I can't hold on.

2009
01:55:45.897 --> 01:55:47.023
-I can't hold...
-We got to go.

2010
01:55:47.148 --> 01:55:48.858
Stay on the light.

2011
01:55:51.903 --> 01:55:53.112
MARGARET:
I can't hold on.

2012
01:55:54.113 --> 01:55:56.449
-(groaning)
-(glass shattering)

2013
01:55:58.952 --> 01:56:00.119
-(loud thud)
-(groans)

2014
01:56:00.203 --> 01:56:01.329
(Margaret gasps)

2015
01:56:01.412 --> 01:56:03.206
-(creaking)
-(grunts)

2016
01:56:03.373 --> 01:56:04.874
DANIEL:
Let's go.

2017
01:56:04.999 --> 01:56:07.043
(device thrumming)

2018
01:56:07.961 --> 01:56:10.088
There. There.
Stay on the light.

2019
01:56:13.257 --> 01:56:15.635
-Stay on the light.
-The light! The light!

2020
01:56:17.971 --> 01:56:20.807
(groaning)

2021
01:56:26.187 --> 01:56:28.731
(groaning)

2022
01:56:33.486 --> 01:56:35.488
(engine starts)

2023
01:56:37.740 --> 01:56:39.534
(siren blaring)

2024
01:56:39.617 --> 01:56:41.661
(urgent chatter)

2025
01:56:43.079 --> 01:56:45.248
SANTIAGO: Hang on.
Grab ahold of something.

2026
01:56:49.002 --> 01:56:50.837
(frantic chatter)

2027
01:56:50.920 --> 01:56:53.047
(engine revving)

2028
01:56:53.089 --> 01:56:55.758
(siren blaring)

2029
01:56:57.301 --> 01:56:59.595
